WEBVTT

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.084
If I Didn't Care

00:00:21.464 --> 00:00:25.342
If I didn't care

00:00:26.595 --> 00:00:30.848
More than words can say

00:00:31.933 --> 00:00:36.103
If I didn't care

00:00:37.314 --> 00:00:41.317
Would I feel this way?

00:00:42.485 --> 00:00:46.531
If this isn't love

00:00:48.284 --> 00:00:52.162
Then why do I thrill?

00:00:53.581 --> 00:00:59.336
And what makes my head
go round and round

00:00:59.420 --> 00:01:04.215
While my heart stands still?

00:01:04.300 --> 00:01:07.928
If I didn't care

00:01:09.305 --> 00:01:12.849
Would it be the same?

00:01:14.769 --> 00:01:20.607
Would my every prayer begin and end

00:01:20.691 --> 00:01:23.610
With just your name?

00:01:25.279 --> 00:01:28.490
And would I be sure

00:01:28.574 --> 00:01:34.454
That this is love beyond compare?

00:01:36.123 --> 00:01:38.166
Would all this be true

00:01:39.585 --> 00:01:44.674
If I didn't care for you?

00:02:02.693 --> 00:02:04.694
Mr. Dufresne,

00:02:04.778 --> 00:02:09.031
describe the confrontation you had
with your wife the night she was murdered.

00:02:13.662 --> 00:02:15.788
It was very bitter.

00:02:15.872 --> 00:02:20.292
She said she was glad I knew,
that she hated all the sneaking around...

00:02:21.712 --> 00:02:25.256
And she said she wanted a divorce in Reno.

00:02:25.340 --> 00:02:27.174
What was your response?

00:02:27.259 --> 00:02:29.218
I told her I would not grant one.

00:02:29.302 --> 00:02:32.346
"I'll see you in hell before I see you in Reno."

00:02:32.431 --> 00:02:36.100
Those were the words you used, Mr. Dufresne,
according to your neighbors.

00:02:37.227 --> 00:02:40.897
If they say so.
I really don't remember. I was upset.

00:02:42.025 --> 00:02:45.527
What happened after you argued
with your wife?

00:02:45.611 --> 00:02:47.529
She packed a bag.

00:02:48.614 --> 00:02:51.783
She packed a bag to go and stay with...
Mr. Quentin.

00:02:51.868 --> 00:02:54.161
Glenn Quentin.

00:02:54.245 --> 00:02:56.329
Golf pro at the Snowdon Hills Country Club.

00:02:56.414 --> 00:03:00.292
The man you discovered was your wife's lover.

00:03:02.045 --> 00:03:03.420
Did you follow her?

00:03:04.672 --> 00:03:06.840
I went to a few bars first.

00:03:06.924 --> 00:03:09.801
Later, I drove to his house to confront them.

00:03:09.886 --> 00:03:13.472
They weren't home, so I...parked in the turnout,

00:03:13.556 --> 00:03:15.140
and waited.

00:03:15.224 --> 00:03:17.434
With what intention?

00:03:17.518 --> 00:03:19.311
I'm not sure.

00:03:19.395 --> 00:03:21.605
I was confused.

00:03:21.689 --> 00:03:23.356
Drunk.

00:03:25.109 --> 00:03:28.111
I think...mostly, I wanted to scare them.

00:03:28.196 --> 00:03:31.448
When they arrived,
you went up to the house and murdered them.

00:03:31.532 --> 00:03:34.618
No. I was sobering up.

00:03:34.702 --> 00:03:37.454
I got back in the car,
and I drove home to sleep it off.

00:03:37.538 --> 00:03:41.000
Along the way, I stopped,
and I threw my gun into the Royal River.

00:03:41.085 --> 00:03:43.294
I feel I've been very clear on this point.

00:03:43.378 --> 00:03:47.173
Well, where I get hazy is where the cleaning
woman shows up the following morning

00:03:47.257 --> 00:03:52.929
and finds your wife in bed with her lover,
riddled with.38 caliber bullets.

00:03:53.972 --> 00:03:58.226
Now, does that strike you as a fantastic
coincidence, Mr. Dufresne, or is it just me?

00:03:58.310 --> 00:04:00.144
Yes, it does.

00:04:00.229 --> 00:04:06.317
Yet you still maintain that you threw your gun
into the river before the murders took place?

00:04:06.401 --> 00:04:10.196
- That's very convenient.
- It's the truth.

00:04:10.280 --> 00:04:14.992
The police dragged that river
for three days, and nary a gun was found.

00:04:15.077 --> 00:04:17.870
So, there could be no comparison made
between your gun

00:04:17.955 --> 00:04:22.125
and the bullets taken from
the bloodstained corpses of the victims.

00:04:23.418 --> 00:04:26.295
And that also...

00:04:26.380 --> 00:04:28.381
is very convenient.

00:04:28.465 --> 00:04:29.966
Isn't it, Mr. Dufresne?

00:04:31.176 --> 00:04:33.427
Since I am innocent of this crime, sir,

00:04:33.512 --> 00:04:37.099
I find it decidedly inconvenient
that the gun was never found.

00:04:38.268 --> 00:04:40.352
If I Didn't Care

00:04:44.274 --> 00:04:47.526
And would I be sure that this

00:04:47.610 --> 00:04:52.239
Is love beyond compare...

00:04:55.785 --> 00:04:58.704
Ladies and gentlemen,
you've heard all the evidence.

00:04:58.788 --> 00:05:01.373
We have the accused at the scene of the crime.

00:05:01.457 --> 00:05:03.292
We have footprints, tire tracks,

00:05:03.376 --> 00:05:07.421
bullets strewn on the ground which bear
his fingerprints, a broken bourbon bottle,

00:05:07.505 --> 00:05:09.631
likewise with fingerprints.

00:05:09.716 --> 00:05:11.383
And most of all,

00:05:11.467 --> 00:05:13.760
we have a beautiful young woman and her lover

00:05:13.845 --> 00:05:15.929
lying dead in each other's arms.

00:05:18.016 --> 00:05:20.267
They had sinned.

00:05:21.895 --> 00:05:25.898
But was their crime so great
as to merit a death sentence?

00:05:27.066 --> 00:05:29.151
Now, while you think about that...

00:05:30.862 --> 00:05:33.363
..think about this.

00:05:33.448 --> 00:05:35.992
A revolver holds six bullets.

00:05:36.076 --> 00:05:37.452
Not eight.

00:05:37.536 --> 00:05:40.997
I submit that this was not a hot-blooded
crime of passion.

00:05:41.081 --> 00:05:44.125
That could be understood, if not condoned.

00:05:44.210 --> 00:05:46.836
No. This was revenge...

00:05:46.921 --> 00:05:51.424
of a much more brutal
and cold-blooded nature. Consider this.

00:05:51.508 --> 00:05:54.052
Four bullets per victim.

00:05:54.136 --> 00:05:56.512
Not six shots fired, but eight.

00:05:56.597 --> 00:06:00.516
That means that he fired the gun empty,

00:06:00.601 --> 00:06:02.894
and then stopped to reload...

00:06:03.979 --> 00:06:06.564
..so that he could shoot each of them again.

00:06:06.649 --> 00:06:09.234
An extra bullet per lover.

00:06:09.318 --> 00:06:11.361
Right in the head.

00:06:15.407 --> 00:06:20.328
You strike me as a particularly icy
and remorseless man, Mr. Dufresne.

00:06:20.412 --> 00:06:22.664
It chills my blood just to look at you.

00:06:24.416 --> 00:06:27.377
By the power vested in me
by the state of Maine,

00:06:27.461 --> 00:06:31.005
I hereby order you to serve two life sentences,
back to back.

00:06:32.091 --> 00:06:34.718
One for each of your victims. So be it.

00:06:59.744 --> 00:07:01.412
Sit.

00:07:05.458 --> 00:07:08.377
We see by your file
you've served 20 years of a life sentence.

00:07:08.461 --> 00:07:10.045
Yes, sir.

00:07:10.130 --> 00:07:12.589
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

00:07:12.674 --> 00:07:14.883
Oh, yes, sir. Absolutely, sir.

00:07:16.511 --> 00:07:18.470
I mean, I learned my lesson.

00:07:19.556 --> 00:07:22.808
I can honestly say...I'm a changed man.

00:07:26.521 --> 00:07:28.856
I'm no longer a danger to society.

00:07:28.940 --> 00:07:31.026
That's God's honest truth.

00:08:07.188 --> 00:08:09.981
Hey, Red. How'd it go?

00:08:10.066 --> 00:08:12.692
Same old shit. Different day.

00:08:12.777 --> 00:08:16.404
Yeah. I know how you feel.
I'm up for rejection next week.

00:08:17.573 --> 00:08:20.158
Yeah, I got rejected last week.

00:08:20.242 --> 00:08:21.534
It happens.

00:08:21.619 --> 00:08:23.203
Hey, Red. Bump me a deck.

00:08:23.287 --> 00:08:26.664
Get the fuck out of my face, will you, man?
You've had five packs already.

00:08:26.749 --> 00:08:27.957
- Four.
- Five.

00:08:29.002 --> 00:08:32.546
There must be a con like me
in every prison in America.

00:08:32.631 --> 00:08:34.548
I'm the guy who can get it for you.

00:08:34.633 --> 00:08:37.760
Cigarettes, a bag of reefer - if that's your thing -

00:08:37.844 --> 00:08:41.430
a bottle of brandy
to celebrate your kid's high-school graduation.

00:08:41.515 --> 00:08:43.849
Damn near anything, within reason.

00:08:43.934 --> 00:08:46.227
Yes, sir. I'm a regular Sears and Roebuck.

00:08:50.565 --> 00:08:53.943
So, when Andy Dufresne came to me in 1949

00:08:54.027 --> 00:08:57.363
and asked me to smuggle Rita Hayworth
into the prison for him,

00:08:57.447 --> 00:08:59.532
I told him, "No problem."

00:09:41.617 --> 00:09:43.910
Andy came to Shawshank Prison

00:09:43.995 --> 00:09:48.123
in early 1947, for murdering his wife
and the fella she was banging.

00:09:48.207 --> 00:09:52.502
On the outside he had been vice-president
of a large Portland bank.

00:09:52.587 --> 00:09:54.588
Good work for a man as young as he was.

00:09:59.969 --> 00:10:01.636
Hey, Red.

00:10:37.799 --> 00:10:41.344
Do you speak English, butt steak?
You follow this officer.

00:10:54.316 --> 00:10:58.694
I haven't seen such a sorry-looking heap
of m-m-maggot shit in all my life.

00:10:58.779 --> 00:11:00.863
Hey, fish! Come over here.

00:11:15.921 --> 00:11:18.798
Come on, fish.

00:11:24.264 --> 00:11:26.181
Taking bets today, Red?

00:11:26.266 --> 00:11:28.267
Smokes or coins? Better's choice.

00:11:28.351 --> 00:11:30.143
Smokes. Put me down for two.

00:11:30.228 --> 00:11:32.271
All right. Who's your horse?

00:11:32.355 --> 00:11:35.649
That little sack of shit...eighth from the front.

00:11:35.733 --> 00:11:36.900
He'll be first.

00:11:36.985 --> 00:11:39.194
- Bullshit. I'll take that action.
- Me too.

00:11:39.279 --> 00:11:41.530
You're out some smokes, son. Let me tell you.

00:11:41.614 --> 00:11:43.532
Heywood, you're so smart, you call it.

00:11:43.616 --> 00:11:46.118
I'll take...t-t-the chubby fat-ass there.

00:11:46.202 --> 00:11:49.580
The fifth one from the front.
Put me down for a quarter deck.

00:11:49.664 --> 00:11:52.541
Fresh fish!

00:11:52.625 --> 00:11:56.712
Fresh fish today! We're reeling them in!

00:11:56.796 --> 00:12:01.049
I must admit, I didn't think much of Andy,
first time I laid eyes on him.

00:12:01.134 --> 00:12:04.636
Looked like a stiff breeze would blow him over.

00:12:04.721 --> 00:12:07.014
That was my first impression of the man.

00:12:07.098 --> 00:12:08.807
What do you say, Red?

00:12:08.891 --> 00:12:12.144
That tall drink of water
with the silver spoon up his ass.

00:12:12.228 --> 00:12:14.396
That guy? Never happen.

00:12:14.480 --> 00:12:15.606
Ten cigarettes.

00:12:15.690 --> 00:12:16.857
That's a rich bet.

00:12:16.941 --> 00:12:19.151
All right. Who's gonna prove me wrong?

00:12:19.235 --> 00:12:21.321
Heywood? Jigger?

00:12:21.405 --> 00:12:22.864
Skeet?

00:12:22.948 --> 00:12:25.158
Floyd?

00:12:25.242 --> 00:12:27.368
Four brave souls.

00:12:27.453 --> 00:12:30.288
Return to your cell blocks for evening count.

00:12:30.372 --> 00:12:32.874
All prisoners return to your cell blocks.

00:12:53.979 --> 00:12:56.064
Turn to the right. Eyes front.

00:13:09.495 --> 00:13:12.497
This is Mr. Hadley. He's Captain of the Guards.

00:13:12.581 --> 00:13:14.749
I'm Mr. Norton, the Warden.

00:13:14.833 --> 00:13:17.335
You are convicted felons.

00:13:17.419 --> 00:13:19.755
That's why they've sent you to me.

00:13:19.839 --> 00:13:21.465
Rule number one:

00:13:21.549 --> 00:13:23.425
No blasphemy.

00:13:23.510 --> 00:13:27.054
I'll not have the Lord's name taken in vain
in my prison.

00:13:27.138 --> 00:13:28.514
The other rules...

00:13:28.598 --> 00:13:30.307
you'll figure out as you go along.

00:13:30.392 --> 00:13:32.184
Any questions?

00:13:32.268 --> 00:13:33.477
When do we eat?

00:13:41.986 --> 00:13:44.154
You eat when we say you eat!

00:13:44.239 --> 00:13:47.616
You shit when we say you shit,
and you piss when we say you piss.

00:13:47.701 --> 00:13:50.577
You got that, you maggot-dick motherfucker?

00:13:50.662 --> 00:13:51.954
Aarghh!

00:13:52.038 --> 00:13:53.997
On your feet.

00:13:54.082 --> 00:13:55.874
I believe in two things.

00:13:55.959 --> 00:13:58.836
Discipline and the Bible.

00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:00.754
Here you'll receive both.

00:14:01.881 --> 00:14:04.508
Put your trust in the Lord.

00:14:04.592 --> 00:14:06.468
Your ass belongs to me.

00:14:08.555 --> 00:14:10.639
Welcome to Shawshank.

00:14:15.770 --> 00:14:17.188
Unhook 'em.

00:14:22.445 --> 00:14:24.320
Turn around.

00:14:30.745 --> 00:14:33.079
That's enough.

00:14:33.164 --> 00:14:35.915
Move to the end of the cage.

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:37.375
Turn around.

00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:38.710
Delouse him.

00:14:39.920 --> 00:14:41.796
Turn around.

00:14:44.383 --> 00:14:47.552
Move out of the cage, go left.
Pick up your clothes and Bible.

00:14:47.636 --> 00:14:49.179
Next man up.

00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:54.476
To the right. Right, right, right.

00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:56.102
Left, left...

00:14:56.187 --> 00:15:00.356
The first night's the toughest.
No doubt about it.

00:15:00.441 --> 00:15:03.568
They march you in,
naked as the day you were born,

00:15:03.652 --> 00:15:07.739
skin burning and half-blind
from that delousing shit they throw on you.

00:15:07.823 --> 00:15:10.784
And when they put you in that cell,

00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:13.536
and those bars slam home...

00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:16.373
that's when you know it's for real.

00:15:16.458 --> 00:15:19.794
Old life blown away in the blink of an eye.

00:15:19.878 --> 00:15:21.086
Nothing left,

00:15:21.171 --> 00:15:23.881
but all the time in the world to think about it.

00:15:25.133 --> 00:15:28.886
Most new fish come close to madness
the first night.

00:15:28.970 --> 00:15:32.264
Somebody always breaks down crying.

00:15:32.349 --> 00:15:34.809
Happens every time.

00:15:34.893 --> 00:15:36.977
The only question is:

00:15:37.062 --> 00:15:38.479
Who's it gonna be?

00:15:39.564 --> 00:15:42.149
It's as good a thing to bet on as any, I guess.

00:15:44.069 --> 00:15:46.153
I had my money on Andy Dufresne.

00:15:55.789 --> 00:15:57.414
Lights out!

00:16:17.937 --> 00:16:21.022
I remember my first night.

00:16:21.107 --> 00:16:23.191
Seems like a long time ago.

00:16:24.735 --> 00:16:27.195
Yoo-hoo!

00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:29.781
Hey, fish.

00:16:29.866 --> 00:16:32.909
Fish, fish, fish, fish, fishy.

00:16:32.994 --> 00:16:36.913
- Boy, are you scared of the dark?
- You like it here, new fish?

00:16:36.998 --> 00:16:39.332
You'll wish
your daddy never dicked your mommy.

00:16:39.417 --> 00:16:43.420
Fishy! Oh, I want me a pork chop. Oh, yes!

00:16:43.504 --> 00:16:48.550
You taking this down, new fish?
There's gonna be a quiz later!

00:16:48.634 --> 00:16:52.012
- Poke your ass out, give me a first look!
- Shh! Keep it down.

00:16:52.096 --> 00:16:55.432
The boys always go fishing
with first-timers.

00:16:55.516 --> 00:16:57.559
They don't quit till they reel someone in.

00:17:00.229 --> 00:17:02.731
Hey, Fat Ass.

00:17:02.815 --> 00:17:04.482
Fat Ass.

00:17:05.693 --> 00:17:08.153
Talk to me, boy.

00:17:08.237 --> 00:17:10.947
I know you're there. I can hear you breathing.

00:17:11.032 --> 00:17:13.951
Don't you listen to these nitwits.
You hear me?

00:17:14.036 --> 00:17:16.120
This place ain't so bad.

00:17:16.204 --> 00:17:17.830
I tell you what.

00:17:18.999 --> 00:17:22.168
I'll introduce you around.
Make you feel right at home.

00:17:22.252 --> 00:17:24.837
I know a couple of big old bull queers

00:17:24.922 --> 00:17:27.882
that would just love to make your acquaintance.

00:17:27.966 --> 00:17:31.385
Especially that big, white,
m- mushy butt of yours.

00:17:31.470 --> 00:17:33.387
God!

00:17:33.472 --> 00:17:34.972
I don't belong here!

00:17:35.057 --> 00:17:36.474
We have a winner!

00:17:36.558 --> 00:17:38.309
I wanna go home!

00:17:38.393 --> 00:17:40.227
And it's Fat Ass by a nose!

00:17:40.312 --> 00:17:43.481
Hey, it's the fat guy! It's the fat guy!

00:17:43.565 --> 00:17:47.401
Fresh fish! Fresh fish! Fresh fish!

00:17:47.486 --> 00:17:50.196
I don't belong here!

00:17:50.280 --> 00:17:51.489
Fresh fish!

00:17:51.573 --> 00:17:54.909
I wanna go home. I want my mommy.

00:17:54.993 --> 00:17:57.995
I had your mother. She wasn't that great.

00:17:58.080 --> 00:17:59.580
Fresh fish!

00:18:01.416 --> 00:18:04.210
What the Christ is this happy horse shit?

00:18:04.294 --> 00:18:07.004
He took the Lord's name in vain.
I'm telling the Warden.

00:18:07.089 --> 00:18:08.589
With my baton up your ass!

00:18:08.674 --> 00:18:10.342
Let me out of here!

00:18:10.426 --> 00:18:13.804
What is your malfunction,
you fat barrel of monkey spunk?

00:18:13.888 --> 00:18:15.055
Please...

00:18:15.139 --> 00:18:17.182
I ain't supposed to be here.

00:18:17.266 --> 00:18:18.642
Not me!

00:18:18.726 --> 00:18:21.186
I ain't gonna count to three, or even one.

00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:23.563
Shut the fuck up, or I'll sing you a lullaby!

00:18:23.648 --> 00:18:25.482
Shut up, man. Shut up.

00:18:25.566 --> 00:18:26.858
There's been a mistake!

00:18:26.943 --> 00:18:30.112
You don't understand.
I'm not supposed to be here!

00:18:30.196 --> 00:18:31.279
Open that cell.

00:18:31.364 --> 00:18:35.534
Me neither.
You people run this place like a fucking prison!

00:18:43.001 --> 00:18:45.043
Son of a bitch.

00:18:49.215 --> 00:18:51.299
Take it easy.

00:19:14.074 --> 00:19:17.452
If I hear so much as a mouse fart in here
the rest of the night,

00:19:17.536 --> 00:19:21.205
I swear by God and sonny Jesus,
you will all visit the infirmary.

00:19:21.290 --> 00:19:23.374
Every last motherfucker in here.

00:19:27.296 --> 00:19:30.965
Call the trustees.
Take that tub of shit down to the infirmary.

00:19:45.272 --> 00:19:49.984
His first night in the joint,
Andy Dufresne cost me two packs of cigarettes.

00:19:50.069 --> 00:19:52.945
He never made a sound.

00:20:08.463 --> 00:20:11.715
Tier 3 North. Clear.

00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:13.967
Tier 2 South. Clear.

00:20:14.052 --> 00:20:15.928
Tier 3 South. Clear.

00:20:16.012 --> 00:20:17.971
Tier 1 North...

00:20:18.056 --> 00:20:20.849
- Tier 1 South. Clear.
- Tier 4 South. Clear.

00:20:20.934 --> 00:20:23.018
Prepare to roll out.

00:20:26.397 --> 00:20:28.482
Roll out!

00:21:21.370 --> 00:21:24.164
Are... Are you going to eat that?

00:21:24.248 --> 00:21:27.167
I hadn't... I hadn't planned on it.

00:21:28.419 --> 00:21:29.460
Do you mind?

00:21:36.802 --> 00:21:39.429
Ah...that's nice and ripe.

00:21:51.025 --> 00:21:53.484
Jake says thank you.

00:21:53.569 --> 00:21:55.987
Fell out of his nest over by the plate shop.

00:21:58.240 --> 00:22:02.786
I'm going to look after him
until he's big enough to fly.

00:22:02.871 --> 00:22:04.663
Oh, no, no. Here he comes.

00:22:07.792 --> 00:22:11.712
Morning, fellas. Fine morning, ain't it?

00:22:11.796 --> 00:22:14.215
You know why it's a fine morning, don't you?

00:22:14.299 --> 00:22:16.717
Come on. Set 'em down.
I want 'em all lined up here,

00:22:16.801 --> 00:22:19.595
just like a pretty little chorus line.

00:22:19.679 --> 00:22:21.764
Yeah, look at that!

00:22:21.848 --> 00:22:24.725
- Look at that. Oh, Lord!
- I can't stand this guy.

00:22:25.936 --> 00:22:28.604
Yes. Richmond, Virginia.

00:22:28.688 --> 00:22:30.773
- Smell my ass!
- After he smells mine.

00:22:30.857 --> 00:22:36.195
Gee, Red, it was a terrible shame
about your horse coming in last, an' all.

00:22:36.279 --> 00:22:39.490
But I sure do love that winning horse of mine,
though.

00:22:39.574 --> 00:22:42.284
I owe that boy a great big, sloppy kiss
when I see him.

00:22:42.369 --> 00:22:45.371
Why don't you give him some of your cigarettes,
instead?

00:22:45.455 --> 00:22:47.248
Lucky fuck.

00:22:47.332 --> 00:22:49.041
Hey, Tyrell.

00:22:49.125 --> 00:22:52.086
You pull infirmary duty this week?

00:22:52.170 --> 00:22:53.879
How's that horse of mine doing?

00:22:53.964 --> 00:22:55.422
Dead.

00:22:55.507 --> 00:23:00.887
Hadley busted his head up pretty good.
The doc had already gone home for the night.

00:23:00.888 --> 00:23:03.640
Poor bastard lay there till this morning.

00:23:03.724 --> 00:23:06.559
By then, hell, there weren't nothing we could do.

00:23:12.358 --> 00:23:13.942
What was his name?

00:23:17.196 --> 00:23:18.571
What did you say?

00:23:20.449 --> 00:23:22.826
I was just wondering if anyone knew his name.

00:23:22.910 --> 00:23:25.620
What the fuck do you care, new fish?

00:23:27.081 --> 00:23:30.458
It doesn't fuckin' matter what his name was.
He's dead.

00:23:49.812 --> 00:23:52.147
Hey...

00:23:52.231 --> 00:23:54.983
Anybody come at you yet?

00:23:56.485 --> 00:23:58.487
Anybody get to you yet?

00:23:59.614 --> 00:24:02.658
Hey, we all need friends in here.

00:24:02.743 --> 00:24:04.660
I could be a friend to you.

00:24:07.122 --> 00:24:08.789
Hey...

00:24:13.628 --> 00:24:15.504
Hard to get.

00:24:17.174 --> 00:24:18.841
I like that.

00:24:25.474 --> 00:24:28.768
Andy kept pretty much to himself at first.

00:24:28.852 --> 00:24:31.312
I guess he had a lot on his mind,

00:24:31.396 --> 00:24:33.606
trying to adapt to life on the inside.

00:24:35.150 --> 00:24:37.860
It wasn't until a month went by
that he opened his mouth

00:24:37.944 --> 00:24:40.237
to say more than two words to somebody.

00:24:42.157 --> 00:24:44.200
As it turned out...

00:24:44.284 --> 00:24:46.202
that somebody was me.

00:24:49.790 --> 00:24:53.959
Officers Russell and Burwell
report to the duty officer.

00:24:55.003 --> 00:24:57.756
I'm Andy Dufresne.

00:24:57.840 --> 00:24:59.925
The wife-killing banker.

00:25:01.761 --> 00:25:03.470
Why did you do it?

00:25:03.554 --> 00:25:05.180
I didn't, since you ask.

00:25:05.264 --> 00:25:08.308
You're gonna fit right in!

00:25:08.393 --> 00:25:11.561
Everybody in here's innocent.
Didn't you know that?

00:25:11.646 --> 00:25:14.981
- Heywood, what are you in here for?
- Didn't do it. Lawyer fucked me.

00:25:17.902 --> 00:25:20.695
Rumor has it you're a real cold fish.

00:25:20.780 --> 00:25:24.533
You think your shit smells sweeter than most.
Is that right?

00:25:24.617 --> 00:25:26.952
- What do you think?
- To tell you the truth,

00:25:27.036 --> 00:25:30.122
I haven't made up my mind.

00:25:30.206 --> 00:25:34.292
I understand
you're a man that knows how to get things.

00:25:34.377 --> 00:25:37.879
I'm known to locate certain things,
from time to time.

00:25:37.964 --> 00:25:40.966
- I wonder if you might get me a rock hammer.
- A what?

00:25:41.050 --> 00:25:42.426
A rock hammer.

00:25:42.510 --> 00:25:44.803
- What is it, and why?
- What do you care?

00:25:46.681 --> 00:25:49.558
Well, if it was a toothbrush, I'd just quote a price,

00:25:49.642 --> 00:25:52.227
but then a toothbrush is a non-lethal object.

00:25:53.646 --> 00:25:55.356
Fair enough.

00:25:55.441 --> 00:25:57.900
A rock hammer
is about six or seven inches long.

00:25:57.985 --> 00:25:59.610
Looks like a miniature pickaxe.

00:25:59.695 --> 00:26:00.820
Pickaxe?

00:26:00.904 --> 00:26:02.989
- For rocks.
- Rocks.

00:26:04.658 --> 00:26:06.826
Quartz?

00:26:06.910 --> 00:26:08.578
Quartz.

00:26:09.830 --> 00:26:12.206
And some mica.

00:26:12.291 --> 00:26:13.458
Shale.

00:26:14.543 --> 00:26:16.127
Limestone.

00:26:16.211 --> 00:26:18.129
So?

00:26:18.213 --> 00:26:20.298
So, I'm a rock hound.

00:26:20.382 --> 00:26:23.593
At least, I was in my old life.
I'd like to be again on a limited basis.

00:26:23.677 --> 00:26:25.803
Or maybe you want
to hammer somebody's skull.

00:26:25.888 --> 00:26:27.346
No, sir.

00:26:28.474 --> 00:26:30.057
I have no enemies here.

00:26:30.142 --> 00:26:32.518
No? Wait a while.

00:26:34.062 --> 00:26:36.230
Word gets around.

00:26:36.315 --> 00:26:39.442
The Sisters have taken quite a liking to you.

00:26:39.526 --> 00:26:41.319
Especially Bogs.

00:26:42.404 --> 00:26:46.616
I don't suppose it would help any
if I explained to them I'm not homosexual.

00:26:46.700 --> 00:26:48.201
Neither are they.

00:26:48.285 --> 00:26:50.995
You have to be human first. They don't qualify.

00:26:56.252 --> 00:27:00.797
Bull queers take by force.
It's all they want or understand.

00:27:00.882 --> 00:27:04.510
If I were you,
I'd grow eyes in the back of my head.

00:27:04.594 --> 00:27:05.928
Thanks for the advice.

00:27:06.012 --> 00:27:07.596
Well, that's free.

00:27:07.680 --> 00:27:09.932
You understand my concern.

00:27:10.016 --> 00:27:12.559
Well, if there's any trouble,
I won't use the hammer.

00:27:12.644 --> 00:27:16.855
Then I guess you want to escape.
Tunnel under the wall, maybe.

00:27:18.316 --> 00:27:20.108
Did I miss something? What's funny?

00:27:20.193 --> 00:27:23.237
You'll understand
when you see the rock hammer.

00:27:25.114 --> 00:27:27.115
What's an item like this usually go for?

00:27:27.200 --> 00:27:30.244
Seven dollars in any rock and gem shop.

00:27:30.328 --> 00:27:33.038
My normal mark-up's 20 per cent.

00:27:33.039 --> 00:27:35.582
But this is a specialty item.

00:27:35.667 --> 00:27:38.252
The risk goes up, the price goes up.

00:27:38.253 --> 00:27:40.212
Let's make it an even ten bucks.

00:27:40.296 --> 00:27:42.172
Ten it is.

00:27:43.258 --> 00:27:45.676
Waste of money, if you ask me.

00:27:45.760 --> 00:27:47.302
Why's that?

00:27:48.388 --> 00:27:51.432
Folks around this joint love surprise inspections.

00:27:53.018 --> 00:27:55.311
If they find it, you're gonna lose it.

00:27:55.396 --> 00:27:57.522
If they do catch you with it, you don't know me.

00:27:57.606 --> 00:27:59.816
Mention my name, we never do business again.

00:27:59.900 --> 00:28:03.027
Not for shoelaces or a stick of gum.
Now, you got that?

00:28:04.530 --> 00:28:05.947
I understand.

00:28:06.031 --> 00:28:07.448
Thank you...

00:28:07.449 --> 00:28:09.075
Mr. er...?

00:28:09.159 --> 00:28:11.619
Red. The name's Red.

00:28:11.620 --> 00:28:12.662
Red?

00:28:12.746 --> 00:28:15.498
Why do they call you that?

00:28:19.169 --> 00:28:21.254
Maybe it's because I'm Irish.

00:28:29.221 --> 00:28:32.265
I could see
why some of the boys took him for snobby.

00:28:32.349 --> 00:28:35.768
He had a quiet way about him.

00:28:35.853 --> 00:28:40.315
A walk and a talk
that just wasn't normal around here.

00:28:40.399 --> 00:28:41.941
He strolled...

00:28:42.026 --> 00:28:46.362
like a man in a park,
without a care or worry in the world.

00:28:46.447 --> 00:28:51.160
Like he had on an invisible coat
that would shield him from this place.

00:28:51.244 --> 00:28:55.414
Yeah. I think it would be fair to say...

00:28:55.415 --> 00:28:57.499
I liked Andy from the start.

00:28:59.252 --> 00:29:02.463
Let's go!
Some of us have got a schedule to keep.

00:29:05.759 --> 00:29:07.843
Move it! Come on. Move it!

00:29:11.473 --> 00:29:14.600
Bob, how are you doing?
How's the wife treating you?

00:29:24.319 --> 00:29:25.778
Easy.

00:29:25.862 --> 00:29:27.946
Keep it moving.

00:29:30.742 --> 00:29:31.992
Red...

00:29:52.515 --> 00:29:56.726
Andy was right. I finally got the joke.

00:29:56.811 --> 00:30:01.314
It would take a man about 600 years
to tunnel under the wall with one of these.

00:30:05.653 --> 00:30:06.778
Book?

00:30:06.862 --> 00:30:08.738
Not today.

00:30:14.078 --> 00:30:16.162
- Book?
- No.

00:30:17.957 --> 00:30:19.165
Hey, Brooksy.

00:30:22.461 --> 00:30:24.546
Delivery for Dufresne.

00:30:31.637 --> 00:30:37.267
Book?

00:30:40.271 --> 00:30:42.397
Dufresne...

00:30:42.481 --> 00:30:44.650
Here's your book.

00:30:49.072 --> 00:30:50.740
Thanks.

00:30:54.578 --> 00:30:57.788
Dufresne! We're running low on Hexlite.

00:30:57.873 --> 00:30:59.957
Get on back and fetch us up some.

00:31:37.162 --> 00:31:39.121
If you get this in your eyes, it blinds you.

00:31:39.206 --> 00:31:41.957
Honey...hush.

00:31:54.013 --> 00:31:56.431
That's it. You fight.

00:31:56.516 --> 00:31:58.099
It's better that way.

00:32:06.526 --> 00:32:09.361
I wish I could tell you
that Andy fought the good fight,

00:32:09.445 --> 00:32:11.988
and the Sisters let him be.

00:32:12.073 --> 00:32:14.074
I wish I could tell you that.

00:32:14.158 --> 00:32:16.243
But prison is no fairy-tale world.

00:32:18.204 --> 00:32:20.330
He never said who did it.

00:32:20.414 --> 00:32:23.458
But we all knew.

00:32:26.796 --> 00:32:29.673
Things went on like that for a while.

00:32:29.757 --> 00:32:32.384
Prison life consists of routine...

00:32:32.468 --> 00:32:34.678
and then more routine.

00:32:37.056 --> 00:32:40.893
Every so often,
Andy would show up with fresh bruises.

00:32:42.062 --> 00:32:44.105
The Sisters kept at him.

00:32:44.189 --> 00:32:48.317
Sometimes he was able to fight 'em off.
Sometimes not.

00:32:48.402 --> 00:32:51.654
And that's how it went for Andy.

00:32:51.738 --> 00:32:54.282
That was his routine.

00:32:54.366 --> 00:32:58.160
I do believe
those first two years were the worst for him.

00:32:58.245 --> 00:33:00.496
And I also believe,

00:33:00.581 --> 00:33:05.126
if things had gone on that way,
this place would have got the best of him.

00:33:05.210 --> 00:33:08.170
But then, in the spring of 1949,

00:33:08.255 --> 00:33:10.256
the powers that be decided that...

00:33:10.340 --> 00:33:13.759
The roof of the license-plate factory
needs resurfacing.

00:33:13.844 --> 00:33:16.596
I need a dozen volunteers for a week's work.

00:33:17.764 --> 00:33:19.891
As you know,

00:33:19.975 --> 00:33:23.686
special detail carries with it special privileges.

00:33:23.770 --> 00:33:25.855
It was outdoor detail...

00:33:27.357 --> 00:33:30.943
..and May is one damn fine month
to be working outdoors.

00:33:31.028 --> 00:33:32.653
Stay in line there.

00:33:32.738 --> 00:33:35.656
More than a hundred men
volunteered for the job.

00:33:40.038 --> 00:33:42.331
Wallace E Unger.

00:33:43.499 --> 00:33:45.959
Ellis Redding.

00:33:46.044 --> 00:33:48.879
Wouldn't you know it?

00:33:48.963 --> 00:33:51.548
Me and some fellows I know
were among the names.

00:33:51.633 --> 00:33:53.717
Andrew Dufresne.

00:33:53.801 --> 00:33:57.346
It only cost us a pack of smokes per man.

00:33:57.430 --> 00:34:00.140
I made my usual 20 per cent, of course.

00:34:00.224 --> 00:34:03.810
So, this big-shot lawyer
calls me long-distance from Texas.

00:34:03.895 --> 00:34:05.604
I say, "Yeah?"

00:34:05.688 --> 00:34:09.399
He says, "Sorry to inform you,
but your brother just died."

00:34:09.484 --> 00:34:11.985
Oh, damn, Byron. I'm sorry to hear that.

00:34:12.070 --> 00:34:13.445
I'm not. He was an asshole.

00:34:13.529 --> 00:34:15.864
Ran off years ago.
Figured him for dead, anyway.

00:34:15.949 --> 00:34:19.910
So, anyway, this lawyer fella says to me,
"Your brother died a rich man."

00:34:19.994 --> 00:34:22.704
Oil wells and shit. Close to a million bucks.

00:34:22.789 --> 00:34:25.248
A million bucks?

00:34:25.333 --> 00:34:27.709
Fucking incredible
how lucky some assholes get.

00:34:27.794 --> 00:34:30.337
Jeez-Louise! Are you gonna see any of that?

00:34:30.421 --> 00:34:33.507
35,000. That's what he left me.

00:34:33.591 --> 00:34:35.509
- Dollars?
- Yeah.

00:34:35.593 --> 00:34:38.721
Holy shit! That's great.
That's like winning the sweepstakes.

00:34:38.806 --> 00:34:40.014
Isn't it?

00:34:40.099 --> 00:34:43.142
Dumb shit. What do you think
the government's gonna do to me?

00:34:43.227 --> 00:34:45.770
Take a big, wet bite out of my ass, is what.

00:34:45.771 --> 00:34:49.941
Poor Byron! Terrible fucking luck, huh?

00:34:50.025 --> 00:34:52.694
Crying shame.

00:34:52.778 --> 00:34:54.445
Some people really got it awful!

00:34:54.530 --> 00:34:56.072
Andy, are you nuts?

00:34:56.156 --> 00:34:58.282
Keep your eyes on your mop, man. Andy!

00:34:58.283 --> 00:35:01.327
Well, you'll pay some tax,
but you'll still end up...

00:35:01.412 --> 00:35:04.247
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Maybe enough to buy a new car. Then what?

00:35:04.331 --> 00:35:06.708
I've got to pay tax on the car.

00:35:06.792 --> 00:35:10.670
Repair, maintenance, goddamn kids
pestering me to take them for a ride...

00:35:10.754 --> 00:35:14.674
And at the end of the year, you figure the tax
wrong, you pay them out of your own pocket.

00:35:14.758 --> 00:35:16.926
I tell you...Uncle Sam!

00:35:17.011 --> 00:35:20.763
He puts his hand in your shirt
and squeezes your tit till it's purple.

00:35:20.848 --> 00:35:23.558
- Andy! Andy!
- What's he doing?

00:35:23.642 --> 00:35:25.977
- Getting himself killed.
- Keep tarring.

00:35:26.061 --> 00:35:29.147
Some brother! Shit.

00:35:29.231 --> 00:35:30.273
Hey!

00:35:33.610 --> 00:35:35.821
Mr. Hadley...

00:35:35.822 --> 00:35:37.281
do you trust your wife?

00:35:38.825 --> 00:35:40.576
Oh, that's funny.

00:35:40.660 --> 00:35:43.537
You're gonna look funnier
sucking my dick with no teeth.

00:35:43.621 --> 00:35:47.082
I mean, do you think
she'd go behind your back, try to hamstring you?

00:35:48.168 --> 00:35:50.044
That's it. Step aside, Mert.

00:35:50.128 --> 00:35:51.628
This fucker's having an accident.

00:35:51.713 --> 00:35:52.880
He's gonna push him off.

00:35:52.964 --> 00:35:57.092
Cos if you do trust her,
there's no reason you can't keep that 35,000.

00:35:57.177 --> 00:35:59.053
- What did you say?
- 35,000.

00:35:59.137 --> 00:36:00.846
- 35,000?
- All of it.

00:36:00.847 --> 00:36:03.182
- All of it?
- Every penny.

00:36:03.266 --> 00:36:05.100
You'd better start making sense.

00:36:05.185 --> 00:36:07.519
If you want to keep the money,
give it to your wife.

00:36:07.604 --> 00:36:11.732
The IRS allows a one-time-only gift
to your spouse for up to $60,000.

00:36:11.816 --> 00:36:13.358
Bullshit! Tax-free?

00:36:13.359 --> 00:36:16.528
Tax-free. The IRS can't touch one cent.

00:36:16.613 --> 00:36:19.198
You're the smart banker what killed his wife.

00:36:19.282 --> 00:36:22.826
Why should I believe a smart banker like you?
So I can end up in here with you?

00:36:22.911 --> 00:36:24.411
It's legal. Ask the IRS.

00:36:24.496 --> 00:36:27.706
They'll say the same thing.
But I feel stupid telling you this.

00:36:27.791 --> 00:36:30.084
I'm sure you would have investigated the matter.

00:36:30.168 --> 00:36:34.255
Yeah, I don't need no banker to tell me
where the bears shit in the buckwheat.

00:36:34.340 --> 00:36:37.383
Of course not, but you do need someone
to set up the tax-free gift.

00:36:37.468 --> 00:36:39.344
It'll cost you. A lawyer.

00:36:39.428 --> 00:36:41.763
A bunch of ball-washing bastards.

00:36:41.847 --> 00:36:45.683
I suppose I could set it up for you.
That would save you some money.

00:36:45.684 --> 00:36:48.061
If you get the forms, I'll prepare them for you.

00:36:48.145 --> 00:36:50.021
Nearly free of charge.

00:36:51.107 --> 00:36:54.484
I'd only ask three beers apiece
for each of my co-workers.

00:36:54.568 --> 00:36:56.986
Co-workers! Get him! That's rich, ain't it?

00:36:57.071 --> 00:37:00.532
I think a man working outdoors
feels more like a man

00:37:00.616 --> 00:37:02.367
if he can have a bottle of suds.

00:37:02.451 --> 00:37:05.495
That's only my opinion...sir.

00:37:08.916 --> 00:37:10.458
What are you jimmies staring at?

00:37:10.543 --> 00:37:11.543
Back to work!

00:37:11.627 --> 00:37:13.586
Let's go. Work.

00:37:21.971 --> 00:37:27.475
And that's how it came to pass...
that on the second-to-last day of the job,

00:37:27.560 --> 00:37:32.231
the convict crew that tarred the plate-factory roof
in the spring of '49...

00:37:32.315 --> 00:37:35.526
wound up sitting in a row
at ten o'clock in the morning,

00:37:35.610 --> 00:37:39.488
drinking icy-cold, Bohemia-style beer...

00:37:39.573 --> 00:37:44.785
courtesy of the hardest screw that ever
walked a turn at Shawshank State Prison.

00:37:44.870 --> 00:37:46.954
Drink up while it's cold, ladies.

00:37:48.331 --> 00:37:52.501
The colossal prick
even managed to sound magnanimous.

00:37:54.254 --> 00:37:58.883
We sat and drank with the sun on our shoulders,
and felt like free men.

00:37:58.967 --> 00:38:02.469
Hell, we could have been tarring the roof
of one of our own houses.

00:38:02.554 --> 00:38:05.848
We were the lords of all creation.

00:38:05.932 --> 00:38:10.477
As for Andy,
he spent that break hunkered in the shade...

00:38:10.562 --> 00:38:13.272
a strange little smile on his face,

00:38:13.356 --> 00:38:15.441
watching us drink his beer.

00:38:22.199 --> 00:38:23.741
Hey...

00:38:23.825 --> 00:38:25.117
Want a cold one, Andy?

00:38:25.202 --> 00:38:26.869
No, thanks.

00:38:26.953 --> 00:38:28.746
I gave up drinking.

00:38:32.585 --> 00:38:35.754
You could argue
he'd done it to curry favor with the guards.

00:38:35.838 --> 00:38:38.673
Or maybe make a few friends among us cons.

00:38:40.927 --> 00:38:44.387
Me, I think he did it just to feel normal again.

00:38:45.473 --> 00:38:47.557
If only for a short while.

00:38:50.436 --> 00:38:52.771
King me.

00:38:52.855 --> 00:38:55.273
Chess. Now, there's a game of kings.

00:38:55.358 --> 00:38:57.901
- What?
- Civilized, strategic.

00:38:57.985 --> 00:39:00.320
And a total fucking mystery.

00:39:00.404 --> 00:39:01.613
I hate it.

00:39:01.697 --> 00:39:03.615
Maybe you'll let me teach you someday.

00:39:03.699 --> 00:39:06.159
Yeah. Sure.

00:39:06.244 --> 00:39:08.370
I thought of getting a board together.

00:39:08.454 --> 00:39:11.248
Well, I'm the right man.
I'm the guy that can get things.

00:39:11.332 --> 00:39:12.832
We might do business on a board.

00:39:12.917 --> 00:39:15.710
But I want to carve the pieces myself.

00:39:15.795 --> 00:39:19.381
One side in alabaster, the opposing side
in soapstone. What do you think?

00:39:19.465 --> 00:39:21.383
I think it'll take years.

00:39:21.467 --> 00:39:24.052
Well, years I got.
What I don't have are the rocks.

00:39:24.136 --> 00:39:26.304
Pickings are pretty slim in the yard.

00:39:26.389 --> 00:39:28.349
Pebbles, mostly.

00:39:32.688 --> 00:39:35.564
Andy, we're getting to be kinda friends,
aren't we?

00:39:35.649 --> 00:39:37.316
Yeah, I guess.

00:39:38.443 --> 00:39:40.861
Can I ask you something?

00:39:40.946 --> 00:39:42.947
Why did you do it?

00:39:44.157 --> 00:39:48.035
I'm innocent, Red. Just like everybody else here.

00:39:52.332 --> 00:39:54.417
What are you in for?

00:39:56.420 --> 00:39:57.420
Murder.

00:39:57.504 --> 00:39:58.921
Same as you.

00:39:59.006 --> 00:40:00.172
Innocent?

00:40:02.843 --> 00:40:04.927
Only guilty man in Shawshank.

00:41:04.405 --> 00:41:05.989
Where's the canary?

00:41:06.074 --> 00:41:07.407
How did you know?

00:41:07.408 --> 00:41:08.575
How did I know what?

00:41:08.659 --> 00:41:11.078
So, you don't know? Come.

00:41:13.831 --> 00:41:15.957
This is where the canary is, Johnny.

00:41:18.336 --> 00:41:22.339
Quite a surprise to hear a woman singing
in my house, eh, Johnny?

00:41:25.260 --> 00:41:27.637
That's quite a...

00:41:27.721 --> 00:41:29.389
surprise.

00:41:31.892 --> 00:41:33.601
Red...

00:41:33.685 --> 00:41:35.478
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

00:41:35.562 --> 00:41:37.397
Here she comes.

00:41:37.481 --> 00:41:40.358
This is the part I like -
when she does that shit with her hair.

00:41:40.442 --> 00:41:43.361
Yeah, I know. I've seen it three times this month.

00:41:43.445 --> 00:41:45.446
Gilda, are you decent?

00:41:45.531 --> 00:41:47.573
Me?

00:41:49.284 --> 00:41:51.327
Hah! God, I love it!

00:41:57.209 --> 00:42:01.003
I understand
you're a man that knows how to get things.

00:42:01.088 --> 00:42:04.966
Yeah, I'm known to locate certain things
from time to time. What do you want?

00:42:05.050 --> 00:42:07.552
- Rita Hayworth.
- What?

00:42:07.636 --> 00:42:09.470
Can you get her?

00:42:10.556 --> 00:42:14.016
So, this is Johnny Farrell.
I've heard a lot about you, Johnny.

00:42:14.101 --> 00:42:15.977
Take a few weeks.

00:42:16.061 --> 00:42:17.270
Weeks?

00:42:17.271 --> 00:42:22.526
Well, yeah, Andy. I don't have her stuffed down
the front of my pants right now, I'm sorry to say.

00:42:22.610 --> 00:42:25.112
But I'll get her. Relax.

00:42:27.365 --> 00:42:28.866
Thanks.

00:42:28.950 --> 00:42:30.951
- It was a surprise, Mr. Farrell.
- It was.

00:42:31.035 --> 00:42:32.077
Sit down.

00:42:32.162 --> 00:42:34.079
Did you tell him what I'm doing here?

00:42:34.164 --> 00:42:36.999
No, I wanted to save that as a surprise, too.

00:42:37.083 --> 00:42:38.750
Hang on to your hat, Mr. Farrell...

00:42:48.845 --> 00:42:51.096
- Take a walk.
- I gotta change the reel.

00:42:51.181 --> 00:42:53.265
I said fuck off!

00:42:58.104 --> 00:43:00.898
Ain't you gonna scream?

00:43:02.275 --> 00:43:04.067
Let's get this over with.

00:43:08.198 --> 00:43:09.823
He broke my fuckin' nose!

00:43:20.336 --> 00:43:24.380
Now...I'm gonna open my fly...

00:43:24.465 --> 00:43:27.425
and you're gonna swallow
what I give you to swallow.

00:43:28.511 --> 00:43:30.303
Then you're gonna swallow Rooster's.

00:43:30.387 --> 00:43:33.223
You broke his nose,
he ought to have something to show for it.

00:43:33.307 --> 00:43:35.517
Anything you put in my mouth,
you're gonna lose.

00:43:35.601 --> 00:43:38.353
No. You don't understand.

00:43:38.437 --> 00:43:41.731
You do that, and I'll put
all eight inches of this steel in your ear.

00:43:41.732 --> 00:43:42.815
All right.

00:43:42.900 --> 00:43:47.529
But you should know that sudden, serious
brain injury causes the victim to bite down hard.

00:43:48.781 --> 00:43:51.199
In fact, I hear the bite reflex is so strong,

00:43:51.283 --> 00:43:56.079
they have to pry the victim's jaws open...
with a crowbar.

00:43:58.916 --> 00:44:00.542
Where did you get this shit?

00:44:00.626 --> 00:44:02.293
I read it.

00:44:03.379 --> 00:44:06.256
Know how to read, you ignorant fuck?

00:44:07.758 --> 00:44:09.634
Honey...

00:44:10.886 --> 00:44:13.263
..you shouldn't.

00:44:15.307 --> 00:44:18.310
Bogs didn't put anything in Andy's mouth...

00:44:18.395 --> 00:44:20.771
and neither did his friends.

00:44:20.855 --> 00:44:24.149
What they did do...
is beat him within an inch of his life.

00:44:25.360 --> 00:44:27.361
Andy spent a month in the infirmary.

00:44:28.405 --> 00:44:30.906
Bogs spent a week in the hole.

00:44:35.370 --> 00:44:36.996
Time's up, Bogs.

00:44:40.667 --> 00:44:42.751
It's your world, boss.

00:44:44.838 --> 00:44:48.257
Return to your cell blocks for evening count.

00:44:48.341 --> 00:44:50.509
All prisoners report for lockdown.

00:45:06.067 --> 00:45:07.359
What?

00:45:19.832 --> 00:45:22.542
Where's he going?
Grab his ankles.

00:45:24.128 --> 00:45:26.630
No! No!

00:45:26.714 --> 00:45:28.089
No!

00:45:28.174 --> 00:45:29.507
Help me...

00:45:29.592 --> 00:45:30.884
Aaarghh!

00:45:33.179 --> 00:45:35.847
Two things never happened again after that.

00:45:35.931 --> 00:45:38.767
The Sisters never laid a finger on Andy again...

00:45:39.977 --> 00:45:42.687
..and Bogs never walked again.

00:45:43.814 --> 00:45:47.233
They transferred him
to a minimum-security hospital upstate.

00:45:47.318 --> 00:45:53.031
To my knowledge, he lived out the rest
of his days drinking his food through a straw.

00:45:53.115 --> 00:45:57.786
I'm thinking Andy could use a nice welcome
back when he gets out of the infirmary.

00:45:58.913 --> 00:46:02.707
Sounds good to us.
I figure we owe him that much for the beer.

00:46:04.085 --> 00:46:06.753
The man likes to play chess.

00:46:06.837 --> 00:46:08.922
Let's get him some rocks.

00:46:41.331 --> 00:46:43.207
Guys...

00:46:43.291 --> 00:46:45.668
I got one. I got one. Look.

00:46:48.088 --> 00:46:50.172
Heywood, that isn't soapstone.

00:46:50.257 --> 00:46:52.466
And it ain't alabaster, either.

00:46:52.551 --> 00:46:54.176
What are you, a fucking geologist?

00:46:54.261 --> 00:46:56.303
He's right. It ain't.

00:46:56.388 --> 00:46:57.638
Well, what the hell is it?

00:46:57.723 --> 00:47:00.266
A horse apple.

00:47:00.350 --> 00:47:03.477
- Bullshit.
- No, horse shit. Petrified.

00:47:09.860 --> 00:47:12.738
Oh, Jesus Christ!

00:47:12.822 --> 00:47:14.781
Oh, damn!

00:47:14.866 --> 00:47:18.827
Despite a few hitches,
the boys came through in fine style.

00:47:20.037 --> 00:47:22.664
And by the weekend he was due back,
we had enough rocks

00:47:22.749 --> 00:47:25.792
to keep him busy till rapture.

00:47:25.877 --> 00:47:28.587
I also got a big shipment in that week.

00:47:28.671 --> 00:47:31.214
Cigarettes. Chewing gum.

00:47:31.299 --> 00:47:32.799
Sipping whisky.

00:47:32.884 --> 00:47:36.428
Playing cards with naked ladies on them.
You name it.

00:47:36.512 --> 00:47:39.473
And of course, the most important item.

00:47:41.225 --> 00:47:43.310
Rita Hayworth herself.

00:48:17.471 --> 00:48:20.306
OK, look alive! Open all tiers.

00:48:20.390 --> 00:48:22.725
Heads up. They're tossing the cells.

00:48:22.810 --> 00:48:25.061
Heads up. They're tossing the cells.

00:48:27.189 --> 00:48:29.065
119.

00:48:30.567 --> 00:48:32.235
123.

00:48:41.703 --> 00:48:43.579
On your feet.

00:48:45.290 --> 00:48:47.166
Face the wall.

00:49:21.661 --> 00:49:23.745
Turn around and face the Warden.

00:49:29.460 --> 00:49:31.545
Pleased to see you reading this.

00:49:32.922 --> 00:49:35.215
Any favorite passages?

00:49:36.259 --> 00:49:41.388
"Watch ye, therefore, for ye know not
when the master of the house cometh."

00:49:42.432 --> 00:49:45.309
Mark 13:35.

00:49:45.393 --> 00:49:48.061
I always liked that one.

00:49:48.146 --> 00:49:49.646
But I prefer...

00:49:49.731 --> 00:49:52.482
"I'm the light of the world.

00:49:52.567 --> 00:49:56.111
He that followeth me shall not walk in darkness,
but shall have the light of life."

00:49:56.195 --> 00:49:58.780
John, Chapter 8, Verse 12.

00:49:58.865 --> 00:50:02.326
I hear you're good with numbers. How nice.

00:50:03.453 --> 00:50:05.537
A man should have a skill.

00:50:07.625 --> 00:50:09.083
Wanna explain this?

00:50:10.169 --> 00:50:13.630
It's called a rock blanket.
It's for shaping and polishing rocks.

00:50:14.673 --> 00:50:16.633
A little hobby of mine.

00:50:27.478 --> 00:50:30.480
It's pretty clean. Some contraband here,

00:50:30.564 --> 00:50:32.649
but nothing to get in a twist over.

00:50:36.487 --> 00:50:38.571
I can't say I approve of this.

00:50:40.074 --> 00:50:41.783
But I suppose...

00:50:43.744 --> 00:50:45.620
..exceptions can be made.

00:50:56.006 --> 00:50:58.299
Lock 'em up!

00:51:00.302 --> 00:51:02.261
I almost forgot.

00:51:02.346 --> 00:51:04.598
I'd hate to deprive you of this.

00:51:04.683 --> 00:51:06.141
Salvation lies within.

00:51:07.227 --> 00:51:08.560
Yes, sir.

00:51:16.861 --> 00:51:19.446
Tossing cells was just an excuse.

00:51:19.990 --> 00:51:23.575
The truth is, Norton wanted to size Andy up.

00:51:37.215 --> 00:51:40.342
My wife made that in church group.

00:51:42.679 --> 00:51:44.013
Very nice, sir.

00:51:45.181 --> 00:51:47.057
Do you enjoy working in the laundry?

00:51:48.685 --> 00:51:50.394
No, sir, not especially.

00:51:50.478 --> 00:51:53.272
Perhaps we can find something more...

00:51:53.356 --> 00:51:55.441
befitting a man of your education.

00:52:03.784 --> 00:52:05.452
Hey, Jake. Where's Brooks?

00:52:05.536 --> 00:52:06.828
Andy.

00:52:06.912 --> 00:52:09.205
I thought I heard you out here!

00:52:10.708 --> 00:52:12.292
I've been reassigned to you.

00:52:12.376 --> 00:52:15.545
I know. They told me.

00:52:15.629 --> 00:52:17.714
Ain't that a kick in the head?

00:52:17.798 --> 00:52:20.300
Well, I'll give you the dime tour.

00:52:20.384 --> 00:52:22.469
Come on.

00:52:22.553 --> 00:52:24.721
Well, here she is.

00:52:24.805 --> 00:52:27.348
Shawshank Prison library.

00:52:27.433 --> 00:52:30.310
National Geographics.

00:52:30.394 --> 00:52:33.229
Reader's Digest condensed books.

00:52:33.314 --> 00:52:35.607
Louis L'Amour.

00:52:35.608 --> 00:52:37.734
Look Magazine.

00:52:37.818 --> 00:52:40.320
Erle Stanley Gardners.

00:52:40.404 --> 00:52:43.948
Every evening,
I load up the cart and make my round.

00:52:43.949 --> 00:52:47.118
I enter the names on this clipboard here.

00:52:47.203 --> 00:52:50.663
Easy-peasy, Japanesey. Any questions?

00:52:50.748 --> 00:52:53.708
Brooks, how long have you been librarian?

00:52:53.793 --> 00:52:58.963
Oh...I come here in '05,
and they made me librarian in 1912.

00:52:59.048 --> 00:53:02.426
And in all that time,
have you ever had an assistant?

00:53:02.511 --> 00:53:05.096
No. No, not much to it, really.

00:53:05.180 --> 00:53:07.098
Well, why me? Why now?

00:53:07.182 --> 00:53:08.682
I don't know,

00:53:08.767 --> 00:53:12.103
but it'll be nice to have some company
down here for a change.

00:53:12.104 --> 00:53:14.188
Dufresne!

00:53:23.490 --> 00:53:25.574
That's him. That's the one.

00:53:33.125 --> 00:53:34.416
I'm Dekins.

00:53:34.501 --> 00:53:36.961
I was er...

00:53:37.045 --> 00:53:41.048
thinking about maybe setting up
some kind of trust fund for my kids' educations.

00:53:43.385 --> 00:53:44.844
Oh...

00:53:44.928 --> 00:53:46.595
I see.

00:53:48.056 --> 00:53:49.932
Well, erm...

00:53:51.309 --> 00:53:52.852
..why don't we have a seat,

00:53:52.936 --> 00:53:55.020
and talk it over?

00:53:57.566 --> 00:54:00.485
Brooks,
do you have a piece of paper and a pencil?

00:54:11.956 --> 00:54:13.665
Thanks.

00:54:13.749 --> 00:54:15.417
So...

00:54:16.669 --> 00:54:19.171
Mr. Dekins...

00:54:19.255 --> 00:54:23.717
And then Andy says to Mr. Dekins,
"Do you want your sons to go to Harvard,

00:54:23.801 --> 00:54:25.927
- or Yale?"
- He didn't say that?

00:54:26.012 --> 00:54:28.680
As God is my witness, he did!

00:54:28.764 --> 00:54:32.142
Dekins just blinked for a second.
Then he laughed himself silly.

00:54:32.226 --> 00:54:34.102
And afterwards he shook Andy's hand.

00:54:34.187 --> 00:54:35.562
My ass!

00:54:35.646 --> 00:54:36.855
Shook his hand.

00:54:36.939 --> 00:54:39.900
Hell, I...I near soiled myself!

00:54:39.984 --> 00:54:44.196
All Andy needed was a suit and a tie
and a little jiggly hula girl on his desk,

00:54:44.280 --> 00:54:45.614
and he would have been:

00:54:45.698 --> 00:54:47.240
"Mr. Dufresne, if you please"!

00:54:47.325 --> 00:54:49.075
Making a few friends, Andy?

00:54:50.119 --> 00:54:52.078
I wouldn't say "friends".

00:54:52.163 --> 00:54:56.167
I'm a convicted murderer
who provides sound financial planning.

00:54:56.251 --> 00:54:58.586
It's a wonderful pet to have.

00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.588
Got you out of the laundry, though.

00:55:00.672 --> 00:55:02.882
Well, it might do more than that.

00:55:02.966 --> 00:55:05.968
How about expanding the library?
Get some new books in there.

00:55:06.053 --> 00:55:08.763
If you're gonna ask for something,
ask for a pool table.

00:55:08.847 --> 00:55:11.307
- Right.
- How do you expect to do that?

00:55:11.391 --> 00:55:16.646
I mean, get new books in here,
Mr. Dufresne, if you please?

00:55:16.730 --> 00:55:18.481
Ask the Warden for funds.

00:55:19.900 --> 00:55:23.194
Son, son. Six wardens
have been through here in my tenure,

00:55:23.278 --> 00:55:26.906
and I've learned one immutable, universal truth.

00:55:26.990 --> 00:55:28.699
Not one of them born...

00:55:28.700 --> 00:55:33.663
whose asshole wouldn't pucker up tighter than
a snare drum when you asked them for funds.

00:55:33.747 --> 00:55:36.040
The budget's stretched thin, as it is.

00:55:36.124 --> 00:55:37.375
I see.

00:55:37.459 --> 00:55:41.003
Perhaps I could write to the State Senate
and request funds from them.

00:55:41.088 --> 00:55:45.466
As far as they're concerned, there's only three
ways to spend money when it comes to prisons:

00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:47.635
more walls, more bars and more guards.

00:55:47.719 --> 00:55:52.139
Still, I'd like to try, with your permission.
A letter a week. They can't ignore me forever.

00:55:52.224 --> 00:55:53.766
Sure can.

00:55:53.850 --> 00:55:56.728
But you write your letters, if it makes you happy.

00:55:56.813 --> 00:55:59.106
I'll even mail them for you. How's that?

00:56:01.025 --> 00:56:04.069
So, Andy started writing a letter a week,

00:56:04.153 --> 00:56:06.238
just like he said.

00:56:10.285 --> 00:56:14.413
And, just like Norton said, Andy got no answers.

00:56:22.255 --> 00:56:27.759
The following April, Andy did tax returns
for half the guards at Shawshank.

00:56:27.844 --> 00:56:30.929
The year after that, he did them all...

00:56:31.014 --> 00:56:33.098
including the Warden's.

00:56:34.475 --> 00:56:38.228
The year after that, they rescheduled
the start of the intramural season

00:56:38.313 --> 00:56:40.397
to coincide with tax season.

00:56:42.692 --> 00:56:46.903
The guards on the opposing teams
all remembered to bring their W-2s.

00:56:46.988 --> 00:56:51.116
So, Moresby Prison issued you your gun,
but you had to pay for it?

00:56:51.200 --> 00:56:52.952
Damn right. The holster, too.

00:56:53.037 --> 00:56:54.287
That's tax-deductible.

00:56:54.371 --> 00:56:55.538
You can write that off.

00:56:55.622 --> 00:56:58.958
Yes, sir.
Andy was a regular cottage industry.

00:56:59.043 --> 00:57:02.086
In fact, it got so busy at tax time...

00:57:02.171 --> 00:57:04.213
he was allowed a staff.

00:57:04.298 --> 00:57:06.758
Hey, Red, can you hand me a stack of 1040s?

00:57:06.842 --> 00:57:09.510
It got me out of the wood shop
a month out of the year,

00:57:09.595 --> 00:57:12.263
and that was fine by me.

00:57:12.348 --> 00:57:15.725
And still...he kept sending those letters.

00:57:21.023 --> 00:57:22.857
Red, Andy.

00:57:22.941 --> 00:57:24.150
It's Brooks.

00:57:24.234 --> 00:57:26.694
Watch the door.

00:57:26.779 --> 00:57:28.363
Please, Brooks.

00:57:28.447 --> 00:57:30.448
- Just calm the fuck down.
- Stay back!

00:57:30.532 --> 00:57:32.575
- Stay back!
- What the hell's going on?

00:57:32.659 --> 00:57:35.745
You tell me. One second he's fine.
Then out comes the knife.

00:57:35.829 --> 00:57:38.289
Brooks, we can talk about this. Right?

00:57:38.374 --> 00:57:40.500
Nothing to talk about, goddamn it!

00:57:40.584 --> 00:57:42.293
I'm gonna cut his fucking throat.

00:57:42.378 --> 00:57:44.253
Heywood? Wait, what's he done to you?

00:57:44.338 --> 00:57:46.464
It's what they done!

00:57:46.548 --> 00:57:47.965
I...I got no choice...

00:57:48.050 --> 00:57:50.719
You're not gonna hurt him.
Even Heywood knows that.

00:57:50.804 --> 00:57:53.430
- Right, Heywood?
- I...I know that, sure.

00:57:53.515 --> 00:57:56.934
You won't hurt him, because he's a friend,
and you're a reasonable man.

00:57:57.018 --> 00:57:58.310
That's right. Right, guys?

00:57:58.395 --> 00:58:01.772
- Yes.
- So, put the knife down. Brooks, look at me.

00:58:01.856 --> 00:58:03.690
Put the knife down.

00:58:04.776 --> 00:58:05.943
Brooks...

00:58:06.027 --> 00:58:08.278
Look at his neck, for God's sake.

00:58:08.363 --> 00:58:10.697
Brooks, look at his neck. It's bleeding.

00:58:12.033 --> 00:58:13.617
It's the only...

00:58:13.701 --> 00:58:15.994
It's the only way they'd let me stay.

00:58:16.079 --> 00:58:18.664
Come on. This is crazy.
You don't want to do this.

00:58:18.665 --> 00:58:20.749
Put it down.

00:58:28.133 --> 00:58:32.845
Come on. Take it easy.
You're going to be all right.

00:58:32.929 --> 00:58:34.304
Him?

00:58:34.389 --> 00:58:38.058
Hell, what about me?
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat.

00:58:38.143 --> 00:58:40.769
Shit, Heywood,
you've had worse from shaving.

00:58:40.854 --> 00:58:43.105
What the hell did you do to set him off, anyway?

00:58:43.189 --> 00:58:45.524
Nothing. I come in here to say fare-thee-well.

00:58:45.608 --> 00:58:48.736
Ain't you heard? His parole's come through.

00:58:50.781 --> 00:58:53.908
I just don't understand what happened in there.
That's all.

00:58:53.993 --> 00:58:56.578
The old man's as crazy
as a rat in a tin shithouse.

00:58:56.662 --> 00:58:58.872
Oh, Heywood, that's enough out of you.

00:58:58.956 --> 00:59:01.958
- I heard he had you shitting in your pants.
- Fuck you!

00:59:02.042 --> 00:59:03.418
Would you knock it off?

00:59:03.502 --> 00:59:05.837
Brooks ain't no bug.

00:59:05.921 --> 00:59:07.797
He's just...

00:59:09.675 --> 00:59:11.509
He's just institutionalized.

00:59:12.845 --> 00:59:14.512
Institutionalized, my ass.

00:59:14.597 --> 00:59:18.892
The man's been in here 50 years, Heywood.
50 years.

00:59:18.976 --> 00:59:20.685
This is all he knows.

00:59:20.769 --> 00:59:23.188
In here, he's an important man.

00:59:23.272 --> 00:59:24.731
He's an educated man.

00:59:24.815 --> 00:59:26.900
Outside, he's nothing.

00:59:29.069 --> 00:59:31.696
Just a used-up con with arthritis in both hands.

00:59:31.780 --> 00:59:34.991
Probably couldn't get a library card if he tried.

00:59:35.075 --> 00:59:37.160
You know what I'm trying to say?

00:59:37.244 --> 00:59:39.996
Red, I do believe you're talking out of your ass.

00:59:41.248 --> 00:59:44.167
You believe whatever you want, Floyd.

00:59:44.168 --> 00:59:46.712
But I'm telling you, these walls are funny.

00:59:48.131 --> 00:59:50.216
First you hate 'em...

00:59:51.760 --> 00:59:53.844
..then you get used to 'em.

00:59:55.472 --> 00:59:58.098
Enough time passes...

00:59:58.183 --> 01:00:01.143
you get so you depend on 'em.

01:00:01.228 --> 01:00:03.562
That's institutionalized.

01:00:03.647 --> 01:00:05.022
Shit.

01:00:05.023 --> 01:00:06.649
You can never get like that.

01:00:06.733 --> 01:00:08.651
Oh, yeah?

01:00:08.735 --> 01:00:11.320
Say that when you've been here
as long as Brooks has.

01:00:11.404 --> 01:00:13.280
Goddamn right.

01:00:15.617 --> 01:00:18.160
They send you here for life.

01:00:18.245 --> 01:00:20.329
That's exactly what they take.

01:00:22.249 --> 01:00:24.333
The part that counts, anyway.

01:00:31.841 --> 01:00:34.009
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

01:00:35.929 --> 01:00:37.763
You go on, now.

01:00:38.848 --> 01:00:43.519
You're free.

01:00:59.412 --> 01:01:01.288
Bye.

01:01:02.373 --> 01:01:04.291
Good luck, Brooks.

01:01:40.870 --> 01:01:43.581
Dear fellas...

01:01:43.665 --> 01:01:47.877
I can't believe
how fast things move on the outside.

01:01:49.296 --> 01:01:52.340
Watch it, old-timer! Are you trying to get killed?

01:01:52.424 --> 01:01:55.760
I saw an automobile once, when I was a kid,

01:01:55.844 --> 01:01:58.763
but now...they're everywhere.

01:02:02.976 --> 01:02:06.562
The world went and got itself
in a big damn hurry.

01:02:22.913 --> 01:02:29.210
The parole board got me into
this halfway house called The Brewer,

01:02:29.294 --> 01:02:33.089
and a job bagging groceries at the Foodway.

01:02:35.133 --> 01:02:40.471
It's hard work, and I try to keep up,
but my hands hurt most of the time.

01:02:40.556 --> 01:02:42.557
Make sure your man double-bags.

01:02:42.642 --> 01:02:44.893
Last time, the bottom near came out.

01:02:44.977 --> 01:02:48.271
Make sure you double-bag, like the lady says.
Understand?

01:02:48.356 --> 01:02:49.815
Yes, sir. I surely will.

01:02:49.899 --> 01:02:53.694
I don't think
the store manager likes me very much.

01:02:56.656 --> 01:03:01.451
Sometimes, after work,
I go to the park and feed the birds.

01:03:01.536 --> 01:03:06.873
I keep thinking Jake might just show up
and say hello.

01:03:06.958 --> 01:03:08.750
But he never does.

01:03:09.836 --> 01:03:15.215
And I hope, wherever he is,
he's doing OK and making new friends.

01:03:18.720 --> 01:03:21.638
I have trouble sleeping at night.

01:03:21.723 --> 01:03:24.516
I have bad dreams, like I'm falling.

01:03:25.601 --> 01:03:27.519
I wake up, scared.

01:03:27.603 --> 01:03:31.606
Sometimes it takes me a while
to remember where I am.

01:03:33.234 --> 01:03:34.693
Maybe I should get me a gun

01:03:34.777 --> 01:03:38.656
and rob the Foodway, so they'd send me home.

01:03:38.741 --> 01:03:41.075
I could shoot the manager, while I was at it.

01:03:41.160 --> 01:03:43.119
Sort of like a bonus.

01:03:44.621 --> 01:03:48.875
I guess I'm too old for that sort of nonsense
any more.

01:03:48.959 --> 01:03:51.002
I don't like it here.

01:03:51.086 --> 01:03:53.755
I'm tired of being afraid all the time.

01:03:53.839 --> 01:03:54.922
I've decided...

01:03:55.007 --> 01:03:56.883
not to stay.

01:04:08.228 --> 01:04:11.731
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss.

01:04:11.815 --> 01:04:13.900
Not for an old crook like me.

01:05:16.923 --> 01:05:20.968
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss.
Not for an old crook like me.

01:05:22.136 --> 01:05:26.181
PS. Tell Heywood
I'm sorry I put a knife to his throat.

01:05:26.182 --> 01:05:28.267
No hard feelings. Brooks."

01:05:38.988 --> 01:05:41.072
He should have died in here.

01:05:46.495 --> 01:05:50.957
What the fuck have you done?
It's a goddamn mess. I'll tell you that.

01:05:55.671 --> 01:05:57.088
What's all this?

01:05:57.172 --> 01:06:01.050
You tell me, fuck-stick.
They're all addressed to you.

01:06:01.135 --> 01:06:02.427
Take it.

01:06:11.395 --> 01:06:12.979
"Dear Mr. Dufresne...

01:06:14.064 --> 01:06:16.065
In response to your repeated enquiries,

01:06:16.150 --> 01:06:20.862
the State has allocated the enclosed funds
for your library project."

01:06:20.946 --> 01:06:22.322
This is 200 dollars.

01:06:23.365 --> 01:06:27.285
"In addition, the Library District
has generously responded

01:06:27.369 --> 01:06:30.079
with a charitable donation
of used books and sundries.

01:06:30.164 --> 01:06:32.248
We trust this will fill your needs.

01:06:32.333 --> 01:06:36.462
We now consider the matter closed.
Please stop sending us letters."

01:06:36.546 --> 01:06:39.381
I want all this cleared out
before the Warden gets back.

01:06:39.466 --> 01:06:41.133
Yes, sir.

01:06:44.888 --> 01:06:46.263
Good for you, Andy.

01:06:48.892 --> 01:06:50.351
Wow!

01:06:51.436 --> 01:06:53.520
It only took six years.

01:06:54.814 --> 01:06:57.691
From now on,
I'll write two letters a week, instead of one.

01:06:57.776 --> 01:07:01.320
Oh, I believe you're crazy enough.
You'd better get all this stuff out,

01:07:01.404 --> 01:07:02.571
like the Captain said.

01:07:02.656 --> 01:07:06.533
Now, I'm gonna go pinch a loaf.
When I come back, this is all gone, right?

01:07:12.707 --> 01:07:14.708
Wow.

01:07:44.782 --> 01:07:47.492
Duettino from The Marriage Of Figaro

01:07:48.953 --> 01:07:51.538
Sull'aria...

01:07:55.167 --> 01:07:56.167
Andy,

01:07:56.252 --> 01:07:57.585
do you hear that?

01:07:57.670 --> 01:08:01.381
#..zeffiretto

01:08:13.602 --> 01:08:21.443
Questa ser� spirera

01:08:51.850 --> 01:08:56.145
Sotto i pini

01:08:56.229 --> 01:09:01.442
Del boschetto

01:09:02.944 --> 01:09:05.321
Sotto i pini...

01:09:05.405 --> 01:09:08.282
Dufresne?

01:09:08.366 --> 01:09:09.950
Dufresne?

01:09:10.035 --> 01:09:12.119
Andy, let me out.

01:09:14.831 --> 01:09:18.375
Andy?

01:09:18.460 --> 01:09:23.631
I have no idea to this day
what those two Italian ladies were singing about.

01:09:23.715 --> 01:09:26.133
The truth is, I don't want to know.

01:09:26.218 --> 01:09:28.303
Some things are best left unsaid.

01:09:32.350 --> 01:09:37.395
I like to think they were singing about something
so beautiful, it can't be expressed in words...

01:09:37.480 --> 01:09:39.856
and makes your heart ache because of it.

01:09:42.068 --> 01:09:44.778
I tell you, those voices soared...

01:09:44.862 --> 01:09:49.407
higher and farther
than anybody in a grey place dares to dream.

01:09:49.492 --> 01:09:52.869
It was like some beautiful bird
flapped into our drab little cage

01:09:52.954 --> 01:09:56.081
and made those walls dissolve away.

01:09:56.165 --> 01:09:58.500
And for the briefest of moments...

01:09:58.584 --> 01:10:01.670
every last man at Shawshank felt free.

01:10:04.173 --> 01:10:06.675
It pissed the Warden off something awful.

01:10:08.094 --> 01:10:09.219
Open the door.

01:10:11.973 --> 01:10:13.890
Open it up!

01:10:15.101 --> 01:10:17.477
Dufresne, open this door!

01:10:19.105 --> 01:10:20.438
Turn that off!

01:10:27.239 --> 01:10:29.991
I am warning you, Dufresne. Turn that off!

01:10:43.839 --> 01:10:45.715
Dufresne...

01:10:46.842 --> 01:10:48.926
You're mine now.

01:10:56.476 --> 01:10:59.228
Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

01:10:59.313 --> 01:11:01.731
On your feet!

01:11:02.941 --> 01:11:05.026
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

01:11:06.528 --> 01:11:10.573
Y- Y-You couldn't play something good, huh?
Hank Williams or something?

01:11:10.657 --> 01:11:13.326
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

01:11:13.410 --> 01:11:15.203
Was it worth it, two weeks in the hole?

01:11:15.287 --> 01:11:16.537
Easiest time I ever did.

01:11:16.622 --> 01:11:19.665
Bullshit!
There's no such thing as easy time in the hole.

01:11:19.666 --> 01:11:22.293
A week in the hole is like a year.

01:11:22.377 --> 01:11:25.088
I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

01:11:25.173 --> 01:11:28.508
So, they let you tote that record player
down there, huh?

01:11:30.637 --> 01:11:32.262
It was in here.

01:11:32.347 --> 01:11:34.014
And in here.

01:11:35.225 --> 01:11:39.478
That's the beauty of music.
They can't get that from you.

01:11:43.399 --> 01:11:45.901
Haven't you ever felt that way about music?

01:11:47.570 --> 01:11:51.657
Well, I played a mean harmonica,
as a younger man.

01:11:51.741 --> 01:11:53.533
Lost interest in it, though.

01:11:53.618 --> 01:11:55.452
Didn't make much sense in here.

01:11:55.536 --> 01:11:57.996
Here's where it makes the most sense.

01:11:58.081 --> 01:12:00.666
You need it, so you don't forget.

01:12:00.750 --> 01:12:02.084
Forget?

01:12:02.168 --> 01:12:04.127
Forget that...

01:12:04.212 --> 01:12:06.296
there are places...

01:12:07.632 --> 01:12:10.175
..in the world that aren't made out of stone...

01:12:10.260 --> 01:12:12.302
that there's a...

01:12:12.387 --> 01:12:14.221
there's something...

01:12:14.305 --> 01:12:17.099
inside that they can't get to...

01:12:17.183 --> 01:12:19.476
that they can't touch.

01:12:19.560 --> 01:12:21.437
It's yours.

01:12:22.856 --> 01:12:24.565
What are you talking about?

01:12:25.651 --> 01:12:27.235
Hope.

01:12:27.319 --> 01:12:29.195
Hope?

01:12:31.031 --> 01:12:33.700
Let me tell you something, my friend.

01:12:33.784 --> 01:12:35.743
Hope is a dangerous thing.

01:12:37.329 --> 01:12:39.372
Hope can drive a man insane.

01:12:40.416 --> 01:12:42.333
It's got no use on the inside.

01:12:42.418 --> 01:12:45.086
You'd better get used to that idea.

01:12:47.506 --> 01:12:49.132
Like Brooks did?

01:13:14.366 --> 01:13:15.408
Sit down.

01:13:20.623 --> 01:13:24.084
It says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

01:13:24.169 --> 01:13:26.795
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

01:13:26.880 --> 01:13:28.964
Oh, yes, sir.

01:13:28.965 --> 01:13:31.050
Without a doubt.

01:13:32.093 --> 01:13:34.428
And I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

01:13:37.015 --> 01:13:39.058
No danger to society here.

01:13:39.142 --> 01:13:41.226
God's honest truth.

01:13:43.563 --> 01:13:45.647
Absolutely rehabilitated.

01:13:55.575 --> 01:13:57.659
30 years.

01:13:58.745 --> 01:14:00.788
Jesus, when they say it like that...

01:14:00.872 --> 01:14:02.956
You wonder where it went.

01:14:05.919 --> 01:14:08.003
I wonder where ten years went.

01:14:13.051 --> 01:14:14.343
Here.

01:14:14.427 --> 01:14:16.595
Little parole rejection present.

01:14:18.432 --> 01:14:20.475
Go ahead and open it.

01:14:20.559 --> 01:14:24.354
I had to go through one of your competitors.
I hope you don't mind.

01:14:24.438 --> 01:14:26.523
I wanted it to be a surprise.

01:14:36.659 --> 01:14:38.743
It's very pretty, Andy.

01:14:39.829 --> 01:14:41.913
Thank you.

01:14:43.666 --> 01:14:45.750
Are you going to play it?

01:14:49.880 --> 01:14:51.965
No.

01:14:54.260 --> 01:14:56.344
Not right now.

01:15:03.602 --> 01:15:05.687
Tier 3 South. Clear.

01:15:06.730 --> 01:15:08.773
Tier 4 North. Clear.

01:15:08.858 --> 01:15:10.942
Tier 1 South. Clear.

01:15:13.779 --> 01:15:15.865
Fall in!

01:15:50.442 --> 01:15:52.026
Lights out!

01:16:26.938 --> 01:16:28.980
Andy was as good as his word.

01:16:29.065 --> 01:16:31.566
He wrote two letters a week instead of one.

01:16:34.195 --> 01:16:38.323
In 1959, the State Senate
finally clued into the fact

01:16:38.407 --> 01:16:41.284
they couldn't buy him off
with just a $200 check.

01:16:41.369 --> 01:16:47.958
Appropriations Committee voted
an annual payment of $500 just to shut him up.

01:16:48.042 --> 01:16:49.751
And you'd be amazed

01:16:49.835 --> 01:16:51.503
how far Andy could stretch it.

01:16:51.587 --> 01:16:54.464
He made deals with book clubs, charity groups.

01:16:54.549 --> 01:16:56.925
He bought remaindered books by the pound.

01:16:57.009 --> 01:16:59.219
Treasure Island.

01:16:59.303 --> 01:17:01.471
Robert Louis...

01:17:01.556 --> 01:17:02.764
..Stevenson.

01:17:02.848 --> 01:17:04.307
Fiction, adventure.

01:17:06.310 --> 01:17:07.936
What's next?

01:17:07.937 --> 01:17:10.647
I got here Auto Repair and...

01:17:11.692 --> 01:17:13.025
..Soap Carving.

01:17:13.110 --> 01:17:16.487
Trade skills and hobbies. Goes under
Educational. The stack behind you.

01:17:16.572 --> 01:17:18.614
The Count Of Monte Crisco.

01:17:18.699 --> 01:17:21.033
That's Cristo, you dumb shit.

01:17:21.118 --> 01:17:24.912
By Alexandree...Dumass.

01:17:24.997 --> 01:17:29.917
Dumb-ass?

01:17:32.421 --> 01:17:34.755
Dumas. You know what that's about?

01:17:34.840 --> 01:17:36.215
Uh-uh.

01:17:36.300 --> 01:17:39.010
You'll like it. It's about a prison break.

01:17:39.094 --> 01:17:43.097
We ought to file that under Educational, too,
oughtn't we?

01:17:43.181 --> 01:17:47.351
The rest of us did our best to pitch in
when and where we could.

01:17:48.604 --> 01:17:50.438
By the year Kennedy was shot,

01:17:50.522 --> 01:17:54.859
Andy had transformed a storage room
smelling of rat turds and turpentine

01:17:54.860 --> 01:17:58.195
into the best prison library in New England,

01:17:58.280 --> 01:18:02.158
complete with a fine selection of Hank Williams.

01:18:02.242 --> 01:18:06.412
Lawd I don't know what I'll do-ooo

01:18:06.496 --> 01:18:09.248
All I do is sit and sigh...

01:18:09.333 --> 01:18:14.087
That was also the year Warden Norton
instituted his famous Inside Out program.

01:18:14.172 --> 01:18:16.882
You may remember reading about it.

01:18:16.966 --> 01:18:20.385
It made all the papers
and got his picture in Look Magazine.

01:18:20.470 --> 01:18:22.137
No free ride.

01:18:22.221 --> 01:18:25.182
But rather a genuine, progressive advance

01:18:25.266 --> 01:18:27.434
in corrections and rehabilitation.

01:18:28.478 --> 01:18:30.812
Our inmates, properly supervised,

01:18:30.897 --> 01:18:33.649
will be put to work outside these walls,

01:18:33.733 --> 01:18:35.817
performing all manner of public service.

01:18:35.902 --> 01:18:39.821
These men can learn
the value of an honest day's labor,

01:18:39.906 --> 01:18:43.575
while providing a valuable service
to the community and...

01:18:43.660 --> 01:18:48.872
at a bare minimum of expense
to Mr. and Mrs. John Q Taxpayer.

01:18:48.956 --> 01:18:51.625
Of course,
Norton failed to mention to the press

01:18:51.709 --> 01:18:55.003
that "bare minimum of expense"
is a fairly loose term.

01:18:55.088 --> 01:18:58.256
There are a hundred different ways
to skim off the top.

01:18:58.341 --> 01:19:00.967
Men, materials, you name it.

01:19:02.011 --> 01:19:04.763
And, oh, my Lord, how the money rolled in.

01:19:04.847 --> 01:19:06.973
If this keeps up, you'll put me out of business.

01:19:07.058 --> 01:19:09.227
- Ned!
- This pool of slave labor you've got,

01:19:09.311 --> 01:19:11.354
you can underbid any contractor in town.

01:19:11.438 --> 01:19:15.400
Ned, we're providing
a valuable community service here.

01:19:15.484 --> 01:19:17.735
Well, that's fine for the papers

01:19:17.820 --> 01:19:19.320
but I've got a family to feed.

01:19:19.405 --> 01:19:21.114
Sam...

01:19:21.198 --> 01:19:23.658
Sam, we go back a long way.

01:19:23.742 --> 01:19:26.077
I need this new highway contract.

01:19:26.161 --> 01:19:28.371
I don't get it, and I go under.

01:19:28.455 --> 01:19:30.498
That's a fact.

01:19:30.582 --> 01:19:32.667
You just have some of this fine pie

01:19:32.751 --> 01:19:34.794
my missus made especially for you,

01:19:34.878 --> 01:19:36.212
and you think about that.

01:19:44.263 --> 01:19:47.181
Ned, I wouldn't worry too much
about this contract.

01:19:47.266 --> 01:19:50.476
It seems to me I already got
my boys committed elsewhere.

01:19:52.354 --> 01:19:54.939
You be sure and thank Maisie for this fine pie.

01:19:56.567 --> 01:19:58.735
And behind every shady deal,

01:19:58.819 --> 01:20:01.028
behind every dollar earned,

01:20:01.113 --> 01:20:04.282
there was Andy, keeping the books.

01:20:05.325 --> 01:20:08.746
Two deposits.
Maine National and New England First.

01:20:08.830 --> 01:20:10.914
Night drops as always, sir.

01:20:41.321 --> 01:20:43.071
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

01:20:43.156 --> 01:20:45.949
- Two suits for dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.
- Yes, sir.

01:20:46.034 --> 01:20:49.787
Tell them if they over-starch my shirts again,
they'll hear about it from me.

01:20:49.871 --> 01:20:51.872
How do I look?

01:20:51.956 --> 01:20:54.666
- Very nice, sir.
- Big charity to-do up Portland way.

01:20:54.751 --> 01:20:56.460
The Governor's going to be there.

01:20:57.879 --> 01:20:59.922
Want the rest of this?

01:21:00.006 --> 01:21:02.090
The woman can't bake worth shit.

01:21:03.468 --> 01:21:05.261
Thank you, sir.

01:21:07.431 --> 01:21:11.184
- He's got his fingers in a lot of pies, I hear.
- What you hear isn't half of it.

01:21:11.268 --> 01:21:13.728
He's got scams you haven't even dreamed of.

01:21:13.813 --> 01:21:15.855
Kickbacks on his kickbacks.

01:21:15.940 --> 01:21:18.817
There's a river of dirty money
running through this place.

01:21:18.901 --> 01:21:22.153
But the problem with having all that money
is you'll have to explain

01:21:22.238 --> 01:21:24.823
- where it came from.
- That's where I come in.

01:21:24.907 --> 01:21:27.408
I channel it, filter it, funnel it.

01:21:27.493 --> 01:21:30.036
Stocks, securities, tax-free municipals.

01:21:30.120 --> 01:21:32.789
I send that money out into the real world.

01:21:32.873 --> 01:21:36.501
- And when it comes back...
- Clean as a virgin's honey pot, huh?

01:21:36.585 --> 01:21:37.794
Cleaner.

01:21:37.878 --> 01:21:41.506
By the time Norton retires,
I'll have made him a millionaire.

01:21:44.260 --> 01:21:48.680
If they ever catch on, though, he's gonna
wind up in here wearing a number himself.

01:21:48.764 --> 01:21:52.016
Now, Red, I thought you had
a little more faith in me than that.

01:21:52.101 --> 01:21:55.395
I know you're good, Andy,
but all that paper leaves a trail.

01:21:55.479 --> 01:21:58.481
Now, anybody gets curious,
the FBI, the IRS, whatever,

01:21:58.566 --> 01:22:01.401
it's gonna lead to somebody.

01:22:01.485 --> 01:22:03.445
Sure it is. But not to me.

01:22:03.530 --> 01:22:05.531
And certainly not to the Warden.

01:22:09.578 --> 01:22:10.870
All right. Who?

01:22:10.954 --> 01:22:12.663
Randall Stevens.

01:22:12.747 --> 01:22:13.914
Who?

01:22:15.000 --> 01:22:19.712
The silent silent partner. He's the guilty one,
Your Honor. The man with the bank accounts.

01:22:19.796 --> 01:22:21.964
That's where the filtering process starts.

01:22:22.048 --> 01:22:25.217
If they trace anything,
it's just going to lead to him.

01:22:25.302 --> 01:22:26.886
But who is he?

01:22:26.970 --> 01:22:29.013
He's a phantom, an apparition.

01:22:29.097 --> 01:22:31.056
Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.

01:22:31.141 --> 01:22:33.309
I conjured him...

01:22:33.393 --> 01:22:35.436
out of thin air.

01:22:35.520 --> 01:22:38.355
He doesn't exist, except on paper.

01:22:41.484 --> 01:22:43.861
Andy, you can't just make a person up.

01:22:43.945 --> 01:22:47.072
Sure you can, if you know how
the system works, where the cracks are.

01:22:47.157 --> 01:22:50.659
It's amazing what you can accomplish by mail.

01:22:50.744 --> 01:22:53.370
Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate,

01:22:53.455 --> 01:22:55.789
a driver's license, social security number.

01:22:55.874 --> 01:22:57.082
You're shitting me?

01:22:57.167 --> 01:22:59.126
If they ever trace any of those accounts,

01:22:59.210 --> 01:23:02.088
they're going to wind up chasing
a figment of my imagination.

01:23:02.173 --> 01:23:04.257
Well, I'll be damned.

01:23:05.551 --> 01:23:07.594
Did I say you were good?

01:23:07.678 --> 01:23:09.846
Shit, you're a Rembrandt!

01:23:09.931 --> 01:23:11.973
You know, the funny thing is,

01:23:12.058 --> 01:23:16.019
on the outside, I was an honest man,
straight as an arrow.

01:23:17.063 --> 01:23:19.439
I had to come to prison to be a crook.

01:23:28.199 --> 01:23:29.574
Ever bother you?

01:23:30.618 --> 01:23:34.037
I don't run the scams, Red,
I just process the profits.

01:23:34.121 --> 01:23:36.164
Fine line maybe but...

01:23:36.248 --> 01:23:38.959
I also built that library

01:23:39.043 --> 01:23:41.670
and used it to help a dozen guys
get a high school diploma.

01:23:41.754 --> 01:23:43.630
Why do you think the Warden lets me do it?

01:23:43.714 --> 01:23:46.466
To keep you happy and doing the laundry.

01:23:46.550 --> 01:23:48.677
Money instead of sheets.

01:23:48.761 --> 01:23:51.471
Well, I work cheap. That's the trade-off.

01:23:57.061 --> 01:23:59.271
Willy And The Hand Jive

01:24:07.072 --> 01:24:08.864
I know a cat named...

01:24:08.949 --> 01:24:11.617
Tommy Williams
came to Shawshank in 1965

01:24:11.702 --> 01:24:13.744
on a two-year stretch for B&E.

01:24:13.829 --> 01:24:15.955
That's breaking and entering to you.

01:24:16.039 --> 01:24:20.668
The cops caught him sneaking TV sets
out the back door of a JC Penney.

01:24:20.752 --> 01:24:22.503
Young punk.

01:24:22.587 --> 01:24:24.630
Mr. Rock'n'roll.

01:24:24.715 --> 01:24:26.382
Cocky as hell.

01:24:26.466 --> 01:24:29.051
Hey, come on, old boys! Moving like molasses!

01:24:29.136 --> 01:24:31.095
Making me look bad.

01:24:31.096 --> 01:24:33.055
We liked him immediately.

01:24:33.140 --> 01:24:35.182
So I'm backing out the door, right?

01:24:35.267 --> 01:24:36.976
And I got the TV like this.

01:24:37.060 --> 01:24:40.896
It was a big old thing. I couldn't see shit.
Suddenly, I hears this voice.

01:24:40.981 --> 01:24:43.024
"Freeze, kid! Hands in the air."

01:24:43.108 --> 01:24:44.775
Well, I just stand there,

01:24:44.860 --> 01:24:47.653
holding onto that TV. So, finally, the voice says,

01:24:47.738 --> 01:24:49.697
"Do you hear what I said, boy?"

01:24:49.781 --> 01:24:52.158
I say, "Yes, sir, I sure did.

01:24:52.242 --> 01:24:55.870
But if I drop this fucking thing,
you got me on destruction of property, too."

01:24:59.959 --> 01:25:02.669
Hey, you've done a stretch in Cashman, right?

01:25:02.754 --> 01:25:06.590
Yeah. Yeah, that was an easy piece of time,
let me tell you.

01:25:06.674 --> 01:25:09.301
Weekend furloughs, work programs.

01:25:09.385 --> 01:25:10.802
Not like here.

01:25:10.887 --> 01:25:13.221
Sounds like you done time
all over New England.

01:25:13.306 --> 01:25:18.393
Yeah, I've been in and out since I was 13. You
name the place, chances are I've been there.

01:25:18.478 --> 01:25:22.481
Perhaps it's time you tried a new profession?

01:25:22.565 --> 01:25:27.652
What I mean is, you don't seem to be a good
thief. Maybe you should try something else.

01:25:27.737 --> 01:25:31.573
Yeah, well, what the hell
do you know about it, Capone?

01:25:31.657 --> 01:25:33.408
What are you in for?

01:25:33.493 --> 01:25:35.118
Me?

01:25:36.621 --> 01:25:38.705
The lawyer fucked me.

01:25:42.418 --> 01:25:45.837
Everybody's innocent in here.
Don't you know that?

01:25:53.304 --> 01:25:57.475
As it turned out, Tommy had himself
a young wife and a new baby girl.

01:25:58.519 --> 01:26:03.648
Maybe it was the thought of them on the streets
or his child growing up not knowing her daddy.

01:26:03.732 --> 01:26:07.568
Whatever it was,
something lit a fire under that boy's ass.

01:26:11.532 --> 01:26:14.784
I was thinking of maybe
trying for my high school equivalency.

01:26:14.868 --> 01:26:17.453
I hear you helped a couple of fellas with that.

01:26:18.664 --> 01:26:20.873
I don't waste time on losers, Tommy.

01:26:22.459 --> 01:26:24.544
I ain't no goddamn loser.

01:26:26.380 --> 01:26:28.464
- You mean that?
- Yeah.

01:26:30.134 --> 01:26:32.176
You really mean that?

01:26:32.261 --> 01:26:33.928
Yes, sir, I do.

01:26:34.012 --> 01:26:36.139
Good. Because if we do this,

01:26:36.223 --> 01:26:38.975
we do it all the way, 100%, nothing half-assed.

01:26:40.102 --> 01:26:42.186
The thing is, see...

01:26:43.355 --> 01:26:45.189
..I don't read so good.

01:26:46.316 --> 01:26:47.525
Well.

01:26:49.278 --> 01:26:51.320
You don't read...

01:26:51.405 --> 01:26:53.490
so well.

01:26:54.951 --> 01:26:56.618
We'll get to that.

01:26:57.704 --> 01:26:59.454
- R.
- R...

01:26:59.539 --> 01:27:00.914
- S.
- S...

01:27:00.999 --> 01:27:03.167
So Andy took Tommy under his wing.

01:27:03.251 --> 01:27:05.669
He started walking him through his ABCs.

01:27:07.338 --> 01:27:09.923
Tommy took to it pretty well, too.

01:27:10.008 --> 01:27:12.968
The boy found brains he never knew he had.

01:27:15.305 --> 01:27:19.099
Before long, Andy started him
on his course requirements.

01:27:19.184 --> 01:27:21.143
He really liked the kid.

01:27:21.227 --> 01:27:24.396
It gave him a thrill to help a youngster
crawl off the shit heap.

01:27:25.440 --> 01:27:27.482
But that wasn't the only reason.

01:27:27.567 --> 01:27:30.027
Prison time is slow time.

01:27:31.070 --> 01:27:33.322
So you do what you can to keep going.

01:27:33.406 --> 01:27:35.657
Some fellas collect stamps.

01:27:35.658 --> 01:27:38.285
Others build matchstick houses.

01:27:39.329 --> 01:27:41.705
Andy built a library.

01:27:42.749 --> 01:27:44.791
Now he needed a new project.

01:27:44.876 --> 01:27:46.919
Tommy was it.

01:27:47.003 --> 01:27:51.216
It was the same reason he spent years
shaping and polishing those rocks.

01:27:51.300 --> 01:27:54.928
The same reason
he hung his fantasy girlies on the wall.

01:27:56.305 --> 01:27:57.805
In prison,

01:27:57.890 --> 01:28:01.017
a man will do most anything
to keep his mind occupied.

01:28:02.478 --> 01:28:06.940
By 1966, right about the time
Tommy was getting ready to take his exams,

01:28:06.941 --> 01:28:08.983
it was lovely Raquel.

01:28:26.252 --> 01:28:27.293
Time.

01:28:33.300 --> 01:28:34.592
Well?

01:28:35.678 --> 01:28:37.220
Well, it's for shit.

01:28:37.304 --> 01:28:39.806
I wasted a whole fucking year of my time

01:28:39.890 --> 01:28:43.059
- with this bullshit.
- It's probably not as bad as you think.

01:28:43.143 --> 01:28:46.854
It's worse. I didn't get one thing right.
It might as well have been in Chinese.

01:28:46.939 --> 01:28:49.441
Let's see how the score comes out.

01:28:49.526 --> 01:28:52.152
Well, I'll tell you how the goddamn score
comes out.

01:28:53.947 --> 01:28:55.864
Two points right there.

01:28:55.949 --> 01:28:57.741
There's your goddamn score!

01:28:57.826 --> 01:29:01.662
Goddamn cats crawling up trees,
5x5 is 25.

01:29:02.747 --> 01:29:04.290
Fuck this place!

01:29:04.291 --> 01:29:05.582
Fuck it!

01:29:24.394 --> 01:29:27.146
I feel bad. I let him down.

01:29:27.230 --> 01:29:29.315
Ah, that's crap, kid.

01:29:29.316 --> 01:29:30.858
He's proud of you.

01:29:30.942 --> 01:29:34.069
We've been friends a long time
so I know him as good as anybody.

01:29:34.154 --> 01:29:37.031
- A smart fellow, ain't he?
- As smart as they come.

01:29:37.115 --> 01:29:39.158
He used to be a banker on the outside.

01:29:39.242 --> 01:29:41.285
What's he in here for, anyway?

01:29:41.369 --> 01:29:42.870
Murder.

01:29:43.997 --> 01:29:45.748
The hell you say!

01:29:47.877 --> 01:29:50.170
You wouldn't think it to look at the guy.

01:29:51.213 --> 01:29:53.673
He caught his wife in bed with some golf pro.

01:29:53.758 --> 01:29:55.842
He greased them both.

01:30:03.726 --> 01:30:05.602
What?

01:30:05.686 --> 01:30:08.063
About four years ago,

01:30:08.147 --> 01:30:11.232
I was in Thomaston on a two-to-three stretch.

01:30:12.485 --> 01:30:15.570
I stole a car. It was a dumb-fuck thing to do.

01:30:16.864 --> 01:30:18.907
About six months left to go,

01:30:18.991 --> 01:30:21.034
I get a new cellmate in.

01:30:21.118 --> 01:30:22.994
Elmo Blatch.

01:30:24.038 --> 01:30:25.622
Big, twitchy fucker.

01:30:25.623 --> 01:30:27.916
Kind of roomie you pray you don't get.

01:30:28.000 --> 01:30:30.043
You know what I'm saying?

01:30:30.127 --> 01:30:32.170
Six-to-twelve, armed burglary.

01:30:32.254 --> 01:30:35.465
He said he'd pulled hundreds of jobs.

01:30:35.549 --> 01:30:37.425
Hard to believe, high-strung as he was.

01:30:37.510 --> 01:30:40.512
You'd cut a loud fart,
he'd jump three feet in the air.

01:30:41.639 --> 01:30:43.681
Talked all the time, too.

01:30:43.766 --> 01:30:46.102
That's the other thing. He never shut up.

01:30:46.186 --> 01:30:48.229
Places he'd been in,

01:30:48.313 --> 01:30:50.981
jobs he'd pulled, women he'd fucked.

01:30:51.066 --> 01:30:53.484
Even people he'd killed.

01:30:55.320 --> 01:30:57.696
People who gave him shit.

01:30:58.740 --> 01:31:00.783
That's how he put it.

01:31:00.867 --> 01:31:02.410
So...

01:31:02.494 --> 01:31:04.578
one night, like a joke,

01:31:05.622 --> 01:31:08.916
I say to him, I say,
"Yeah, Elmo, who did you kill?"

01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:10.793
So he says...

01:31:10.877 --> 01:31:14.505
I got me this job one time
bussing tables at a country club.

01:31:15.632 --> 01:31:19.218
So I could case
all these big rich pricks that come in.

01:31:21.638 --> 01:31:23.639
So I pick out this guy,

01:31:24.683 --> 01:31:27.268
go in one night and do his place.

01:31:29.438 --> 01:31:31.439
He wakes up.

01:31:31.523 --> 01:31:33.566
He gives me shit.

01:31:34.609 --> 01:31:36.694
So I killed him.

01:31:37.737 --> 01:31:39.822
Him and this tasty bitch he was with.

01:31:42.117 --> 01:31:44.035
That's the best part.

01:31:45.079 --> 01:31:48.290
She's fucking this prick, see, this golf pro.

01:31:48.374 --> 01:31:50.459
But she's married to some other guy.

01:31:51.502 --> 01:31:53.587
Some hotshot banker.

01:31:55.381 --> 01:31:57.466
And he's the one they pinned it on.

01:32:08.603 --> 01:32:12.439
I have to say
that's the most amazing story I ever heard.

01:32:14.066 --> 01:32:16.943
What amazes me most is
you were taken in by it.

01:32:17.028 --> 01:32:18.653
Sir?

01:32:18.738 --> 01:32:20.405
Well...

01:32:20.490 --> 01:32:23.867
it's obvious this fella Williams
is impressed with you.

01:32:23.951 --> 01:32:26.036
He hears your tale of woe

01:32:26.120 --> 01:32:29.039
and quite naturally wants to cheer you up.

01:32:29.123 --> 01:32:31.166
He's young, not terribly bright.

01:32:31.250 --> 01:32:35.128
Not surprising he wouldn't know
what a state he'd put you in.

01:32:35.213 --> 01:32:37.339
Sir, he's telling the truth.

01:32:37.423 --> 01:32:41.469
Well, let's say, for the moment,
this Blatch does exist.

01:32:41.553 --> 01:32:44.680
You think he'd just fall to his knees and cry,

01:32:44.765 --> 01:32:46.974
"Yes, I did it! I confess!

01:32:47.059 --> 01:32:49.268
And by the way,
add a life term to my sentence"?

01:32:49.353 --> 01:32:52.522
That doesn't matter.
With Tommy's testimony, I can get a new trial.

01:32:52.606 --> 01:32:55.816
That's assuming Blatch is even still there.

01:32:55.901 --> 01:32:57.944
The chances are he'd be released by now.

01:32:58.028 --> 01:33:00.613
They'd have his last address,
names of relatives.

01:33:00.697 --> 01:33:02.865
There's a chance, isn't there?

01:33:04.910 --> 01:33:06.786
How can you be so obtuse?

01:33:06.870 --> 01:33:08.371
What?

01:33:09.873 --> 01:33:11.707
What did you call me?

01:33:11.792 --> 01:33:13.626
Obtuse. Is it deliberate?

01:33:13.710 --> 01:33:15.503
Son, you're forgetting yourself.

01:33:15.587 --> 01:33:18.422
The country club will have his old timecards,

01:33:18.507 --> 01:33:20.633
records, W-2s,

01:33:20.717 --> 01:33:24.720
- with his name on them.
- If you indulge this fantasy, that's your business.

01:33:24.805 --> 01:33:28.766
- Don't make it mine. This meeting is over.
- Sir, if I were to ever get out,

01:33:28.850 --> 01:33:33.854
I would never mention what goes on in here.
I'd be as indictable as you for laundering money.

01:33:35.649 --> 01:33:38.651
Don't ever mention money to me again,
you sorry son of a bitch!

01:33:38.736 --> 01:33:40.612
Not in this office.

01:33:40.613 --> 01:33:42.739
Not anywhere! Get in here now.

01:33:42.824 --> 01:33:46.076
I'm just trying to set your mind at ease,
that's all. Sir, I...

01:33:46.160 --> 01:33:47.536
Solitary. A month.

01:33:47.620 --> 01:33:49.788
- Yes, sir.
- What's the matter with you?

01:33:49.872 --> 01:33:53.125
- Get him out of here.
- This is my chance to get out! Don't you see?

01:33:53.126 --> 01:33:55.127
It's my life! Don't you understand?

01:33:55.211 --> 01:33:57.671
- Get him out! Get him out!
- This is my life!

01:33:57.755 --> 01:33:59.006
No!

01:33:59.090 --> 01:34:00.924
A month in the hole.

01:34:01.009 --> 01:34:03.594
It's the longest damn stretch I ever heard of.

01:34:03.678 --> 01:34:05.470
It's all my fault.

01:34:05.555 --> 01:34:06.972
Oh, bullshit.

01:34:07.056 --> 01:34:10.350
You didn't pull the trigger
and you certainly didn't convict him.

01:34:10.435 --> 01:34:12.811
Red, are you saying that Andy is innocent?

01:34:12.895 --> 01:34:15.063
I mean, for real innocent?

01:34:15.148 --> 01:34:17.190
It looks that way.

01:34:17.275 --> 01:34:19.318
Sweet Jesus.

01:34:19.402 --> 01:34:21.445
How long's he been here now?

01:34:21.529 --> 01:34:23.572
1947. What is that?

01:34:23.656 --> 01:34:25.198
- 19 years.
19 years...

01:34:25.283 --> 01:34:27.909
Williams, Thomas.
- Yeah, over here.

01:34:30.288 --> 01:34:32.539
- Paxon, Edward.
- Yeah.

01:34:33.750 --> 01:34:36.668
What you got? Board of Education.

01:34:36.753 --> 01:34:39.422
- The son of a bitch mailed it.
- Looks like he did.

01:34:39.506 --> 01:34:42.550
Are you gonna open it or stand there
with your thumb up your butt?

01:34:42.635 --> 01:34:44.719
The thumb up my butt sounds better.

01:34:45.763 --> 01:34:48.514
Hey, Skeet, come on,
give me that, you shithead.

01:34:49.558 --> 01:34:51.768
- Floyd, come on.
- Over here, over here!

01:34:52.811 --> 01:34:54.896
Hey, Red!

01:34:56.023 --> 01:34:58.441
Come on, will you throw that away, please?

01:35:04.031 --> 01:35:06.115
Well, shit.

01:35:18.337 --> 01:35:21.047
The kid passed. C+ average.

01:35:21.131 --> 01:35:23.216
Thought you'd like to know.

01:35:39.776 --> 01:35:41.860
The Warden wants to talk.

01:35:55.250 --> 01:35:56.375
Out here?

01:35:56.459 --> 01:35:58.544
That's what the man said.

01:36:14.853 --> 01:36:16.645
Warden?

01:36:16.730 --> 01:36:18.814
Tommy.

01:36:24.279 --> 01:36:25.738
Tommy...

01:36:25.822 --> 01:36:29.908
I'm asking you to keep this conversation
just between us.

01:36:31.327 --> 01:36:33.413
I feel awkward enough as it is.

01:36:51.891 --> 01:36:53.975
We got a situation here.

01:36:55.019 --> 01:36:57.061
I think you can appreciate that.

01:36:57.146 --> 01:36:58.605
Yes, sir.

01:36:58.689 --> 01:37:00.190
I sure can.

01:37:00.274 --> 01:37:04.319
I tell you, son, this thing really came along
and knocked my wind out.

01:37:06.030 --> 01:37:08.573
It's got me up nights, that's the truth.

01:37:10.785 --> 01:37:12.869
The right thing to do.

01:37:14.205 --> 01:37:17.207
Sometimes it's hard to know what that is.

01:37:18.918 --> 01:37:20.960
You understand?

01:37:22.338 --> 01:37:24.422
I need your help, son.

01:37:25.841 --> 01:37:27.926
If I'm going to move on this,

01:37:27.927 --> 01:37:30.678
there can't be the least little shred of doubt.

01:37:32.224 --> 01:37:35.643
I have to know
if what you told Dufresne was the truth.

01:37:35.727 --> 01:37:37.311
Yes, sir.

01:37:37.312 --> 01:37:38.938
Absolutely.

01:37:39.022 --> 01:37:42.107
Would you be willing
to swear before a judge and jury,

01:37:42.192 --> 01:37:44.610
having placed your hand on the Good Book

01:37:44.611 --> 01:37:47.321
and taken an oath before Almighty God himself?

01:37:47.405 --> 01:37:49.532
Just give me that chance.

01:37:53.453 --> 01:37:55.120
That's what I thought.

01:38:42.211 --> 01:38:44.296
I'm sure by now you've heard...

01:38:45.548 --> 01:38:46.923
A terrible thing.

01:38:48.384 --> 01:38:51.970
A man that young, less than a year to go,
trying to escape.

01:38:53.055 --> 01:38:55.682
It broke Captain Hadley's heart to shoot him.

01:38:56.726 --> 01:38:58.810
Truly, it did.

01:39:00.855 --> 01:39:02.939
We just have to put it behind us.

01:39:05.109 --> 01:39:06.526
Move on.

01:39:07.987 --> 01:39:09.863
I'm done.

01:39:10.907 --> 01:39:12.991
Everything stops.

01:39:14.035 --> 01:39:16.870
Get someone else to run your scams.

01:39:18.205 --> 01:39:20.290
Nothing stops.

01:39:21.334 --> 01:39:23.418
Nothing.

01:39:25.171 --> 01:39:27.256
Or you will do the hardest time there is.

01:39:29.134 --> 01:39:31.719
No more protection from the guards.

01:39:31.803 --> 01:39:34.138
I'll pull you out of that one-bunk Hilton

01:39:34.222 --> 01:39:36.390
and cast you down with the Sodomites.

01:39:38.143 --> 01:39:40.645
You'll think you've been fucked by a train.

01:39:41.939 --> 01:39:43.981
And the library?

01:39:44.066 --> 01:39:45.191
Gone.

01:39:45.275 --> 01:39:47.652
Sealed off, brick by brick.

01:39:48.695 --> 01:39:51.489
We'll have us a little book barbecue in the yard.

01:39:51.573 --> 01:39:53.616
They'll see the flames for miles.

01:39:53.700 --> 01:39:56.202
We'll dance around it like wild Injuns.

01:39:57.788 --> 01:39:59.705
You understand me?

01:39:59.790 --> 01:40:01.874
Catching my drift?

01:40:04.962 --> 01:40:07.046
Or am I being obtuse?

01:40:18.183 --> 01:40:20.309
Give him another month to think about it.

01:41:07.900 --> 01:41:10.944
My wife used to say I'm a hard man to know.

01:41:11.029 --> 01:41:13.113
Like a closed book.

01:41:14.323 --> 01:41:17.075
Complained about it all the time.

01:41:17.160 --> 01:41:19.244
She was beautiful.

01:41:21.456 --> 01:41:23.541
God, I loved her.

01:41:26.545 --> 01:41:28.880
I just didn't know how to show it, that's all.

01:41:31.383 --> 01:41:33.468
I killed her, Red.

01:41:34.928 --> 01:41:37.013
I didn't pull the trigger.

01:41:38.432 --> 01:41:40.516
But I drove her away.

01:41:41.727 --> 01:41:44.270
That's why she died, because of me.

01:41:44.354 --> 01:41:46.439
The way I am.

01:41:54.782 --> 01:41:56.866
That don't make you a murderer.

01:42:00.079 --> 01:42:02.163
A bad husband, maybe.

01:42:05.542 --> 01:42:08.920
Feel bad about it if you want to,
but you didn't pull the trigger.

01:42:09.004 --> 01:42:10.421
No, I didn't.

01:42:10.506 --> 01:42:12.548
Somebody else did.

01:42:13.842 --> 01:42:15.927
And I wound up in here.

01:42:18.305 --> 01:42:20.389
Bad luck, I guess.

01:42:23.311 --> 01:42:25.020
Yeah.

01:42:25.105 --> 01:42:27.397
It floats around.

01:42:27.482 --> 01:42:29.942
It's got to land on somebody.

01:42:30.026 --> 01:42:32.277
It was my turn, that's all.

01:42:33.363 --> 01:42:35.823
I was in the path of the tornado.

01:42:42.413 --> 01:42:46.166
I just didn't expect
the storm would last as long as it has.

01:42:50.255 --> 01:42:52.172
Do you think you'll ever get out of here?

01:42:53.424 --> 01:42:55.092
Me?

01:42:57.387 --> 01:42:58.846
Yeah.

01:42:59.889 --> 01:43:01.849
One day, when I've got a long, white beard

01:43:01.933 --> 01:43:05.435
and two or three marbles rolling around upstairs,
they'll let me out.

01:43:07.355 --> 01:43:09.439
I tell you where I'd go.

01:43:10.650 --> 01:43:12.276
Zihuatanejo.

01:43:12.360 --> 01:43:14.278
Zi...what?

01:43:14.362 --> 01:43:16.405
Zihuatanejo.

01:43:16.489 --> 01:43:18.574
It's in Mexico.

01:43:20.369 --> 01:43:22.579
A little place on the Pacific Ocean.

01:43:23.831 --> 01:43:26.207
You know what the Mexicans say
about the Pacific?

01:43:26.292 --> 01:43:27.750
No.

01:43:27.835 --> 01:43:29.919
They say it has no memory.

01:43:32.381 --> 01:43:34.924
That's where I want to live the rest of my life.

01:43:36.510 --> 01:43:38.595
A warm place with no memory.

01:43:41.891 --> 01:43:44.184
Open up a little hotel,

01:43:46.020 --> 01:43:47.896
right on the beach.

01:43:47.980 --> 01:43:50.023
Buy some worthless old boat,

01:43:50.107 --> 01:43:52.192
fix it up new.

01:43:55.154 --> 01:43:56.362
Take my guests out.

01:43:56.447 --> 01:43:58.531
Charter fishing.

01:44:02.453 --> 01:44:05.079
Zihuatanejo, huh?

01:44:07.708 --> 01:44:11.586
In a place like that, I could use a man
who knows how to get things.

01:44:18.011 --> 01:44:20.721
I don't think I could make it on the outside, Andy.

01:44:27.479 --> 01:44:29.563
I've been in here most of my life.

01:44:31.066 --> 01:44:32.858
I'm an institutional man now.

01:44:32.943 --> 01:44:35.027
Just like Brooks was.

01:44:36.446 --> 01:44:38.697
Well, you underestimate yourself.

01:44:38.782 --> 01:44:40.866
I don't think so.

01:44:43.495 --> 01:44:47.706
I mean...in here, I'm the guy
who can get things for you, sure.

01:44:47.791 --> 01:44:51.710
But outside, all you need is the Yellow Pages.

01:44:51.795 --> 01:44:54.213
Hell, I wouldn't even know where to begin.

01:44:56.299 --> 01:44:58.634
The Pacific Ocean?

01:44:58.718 --> 01:45:00.761
Shit.

01:45:00.845 --> 01:45:04.014
- About scare me to death, something that big.
- Not me.

01:45:04.099 --> 01:45:07.559
I didn't shoot my wife and I didn't shoot her lover.

01:45:09.479 --> 01:45:13.107
Whatever mistakes I've made,
I've paid for them and then some.

01:45:13.191 --> 01:45:15.359
That hotel, that boat.

01:45:16.946 --> 01:45:19.114
I don't think that's too much to ask.

01:45:23.744 --> 01:45:26.621
I don't think you ought to be
doing this to yourself, Andy.

01:45:26.706 --> 01:45:28.748
These are just shitty pipe dreams.

01:45:28.833 --> 01:45:31.793
I mean, Mexico is way the hell down there
and you're in here.

01:45:31.877 --> 01:45:33.920
And that's the way it is.

01:45:34.005 --> 01:45:36.631
Yeah, right. That's the way it is.

01:45:38.384 --> 01:45:40.468
It's down there and I'm in here.

01:45:43.180 --> 01:45:45.974
I guess it comes down to a simple choice, really.

01:45:48.811 --> 01:45:50.854
Get busy living

01:45:50.938 --> 01:45:53.857
or get busy dying.

01:45:57.653 --> 01:45:59.738
Andy.

01:46:02.199 --> 01:46:04.284
Red.

01:46:05.328 --> 01:46:07.746
If you ever get out of here, do me a favor.

01:46:07.830 --> 01:46:09.664
Sure, Andy.

01:46:09.749 --> 01:46:11.082
Anything.

01:46:12.168 --> 01:46:15.629
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.
You know where Buxton is?

01:46:17.632 --> 01:46:21.427
- Well, just... There's a lot of hayfields up there.
- One in particular.

01:46:21.511 --> 01:46:23.554
It's got a long rock wall

01:46:23.638 --> 01:46:25.556
with a big oak tree at the north end.

01:46:25.640 --> 01:46:28.351
It's like something out of a Robert Frost poem.

01:46:29.728 --> 01:46:32.438
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.

01:46:33.648 --> 01:46:37.443
We went there for a picnic
and made love under that oak.

01:46:38.945 --> 01:46:41.030
I asked and she said yes.

01:46:45.160 --> 01:46:47.203
Promise me, Red,

01:46:47.287 --> 01:46:49.288
if you ever get out,

01:46:49.373 --> 01:46:51.415
find that spot.

01:46:52.459 --> 01:46:57.922
At the base of that wall, you'll find a rock that has
no earthly business in a Maine hayfield.

01:46:58.006 --> 01:47:00.508
A piece of black, volcanic glass.

01:47:03.678 --> 01:47:06.472
There's something buried under it
I want you to have.

01:47:06.556 --> 01:47:08.557
What, Andy?

01:47:08.642 --> 01:47:10.726
What's buried under there?

01:47:12.522 --> 01:47:15.899
You'll have to pry it up to see.

01:47:21.239 --> 01:47:23.323
No, I'm telling you, the guy is...

01:47:24.367 --> 01:47:26.451
He's talking funnier.

01:47:26.536 --> 01:47:29.913
- I'm really worried about him.
- We ought to keep an eye on him.

01:47:29.997 --> 01:47:34.042
That's fine during the day,
but at night he's got that cell all to himself.

01:47:35.128 --> 01:47:36.586
Oh, Lord.

01:47:36.671 --> 01:47:38.713
What?

01:47:40.383 --> 01:47:42.717
Andy come down to the loading dock today.

01:47:42.802 --> 01:47:46.304
- He asked me for a length of rope.
- Rope?

01:47:46.389 --> 01:47:48.223
Six feet long.

01:47:48.307 --> 01:47:49.766
And you gave it to him?

01:47:49.851 --> 01:47:52.519
Sure I did. Why wouldn't I?

01:47:52.520 --> 01:47:54.229
Jesus, Heywood.

01:47:54.313 --> 01:47:56.565
Hey, how the hell was I supposed to know?

01:47:56.649 --> 01:47:58.567
Remember Brooks Hatlen?

01:47:58.651 --> 01:47:59.693
No.

01:48:00.736 --> 01:48:02.946
Andy would never do that.

01:48:02.947 --> 01:48:05.031
Never.

01:48:06.075 --> 01:48:08.160
I don't know.

01:48:10.205 --> 01:48:12.290
Every man has his breaking point.

01:48:14.918 --> 01:48:16.169
Lickety-split.

01:48:16.253 --> 01:48:19.130
- I want to get home.
- Just about finished, sir.

01:48:35.230 --> 01:48:37.315
Three deposits tonight.

01:48:45.699 --> 01:48:47.783
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

01:48:47.784 --> 01:48:51.245
And shine my shoes.
I want 'em looking like mirrors.

01:48:51.330 --> 01:48:52.705
Yes, sir.

01:48:58.003 --> 01:48:59.670
It's good having you back, Andy.

01:48:59.755 --> 01:49:02.507
The place wasn't the same without you.

01:49:49.556 --> 01:49:52.307
Lights out!

01:50:23.048 --> 01:50:25.341
I've had some long nights in stir.

01:50:26.385 --> 01:50:29.095
Alone in the dark with nothing but your thoughts,

01:50:29.179 --> 01:50:31.014
time can draw out like a blade.

01:50:37.396 --> 01:50:39.731
That was the longest night of my life.

01:50:55.873 --> 01:50:57.498
Give me a count.

01:51:01.837 --> 01:51:03.880
Tier 3 South. Clear.

01:51:03.964 --> 01:51:05.299
Tier 4 North. Clear.

01:51:05.383 --> 01:51:08.969
- Tier 3 North. Clear.
- Man missing on Tier 2.

01:51:09.054 --> 01:51:12.139
- Cell 245.
- Dufresne.

01:51:12.223 --> 01:51:15.142
Get your ass out here, boy.
You're holding up the show.

01:51:17.646 --> 01:51:21.690
Don't make me come down there.
I'll thump your skull for you.

01:51:29.282 --> 01:51:32.660
Damn it, Dufresne, you're putting me behind!
I got a schedule to keep.

01:51:32.744 --> 01:51:35.829
You'd better be sick or dead in there,
I shit you not!

01:51:35.914 --> 01:51:37.748
You hear me?

01:51:44.255 --> 01:51:46.340
Oh, my holy God.

01:52:03.192 --> 01:52:05.902
I want every man on this cell block questioned.

01:52:05.903 --> 01:52:08.113
- Start with that friend of his.
- Who?

01:52:08.197 --> 01:52:09.406
Him!

01:52:11.325 --> 01:52:13.410
Open 237.

01:52:16.414 --> 01:52:18.540
What do you mean, he just wasn't here?

01:52:18.624 --> 01:52:20.166
Don't say that to me, Haig.

01:52:20.251 --> 01:52:22.502
Don't say that to me again.

01:52:22.586 --> 01:52:23.670
But, sir, he wasn't.

01:52:23.754 --> 01:52:25.922
I can see that, Haig!

01:52:26.006 --> 01:52:27.799
You think I'm blind?

01:52:27.800 --> 01:52:30.927
Is that what you're saying? Am I blind, Haig?

01:52:31.011 --> 01:52:32.011
No, sir.

01:52:32.096 --> 01:52:34.139
What about you?

01:52:34.223 --> 01:52:36.057
Are you blind?

01:52:36.142 --> 01:52:38.685
- Tell me what this is.
- Last night's count.

01:52:38.769 --> 01:52:42.063
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. See? Right there.

01:52:42.148 --> 01:52:44.023
Dufresne.

01:52:45.276 --> 01:52:46.943
He was in his cell at lights out.

01:52:47.027 --> 01:52:50.238
It stands to reason
he'd still be here in the morning.

01:52:51.323 --> 01:52:53.199
I want him found.

01:52:53.284 --> 01:52:55.869
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast.

01:52:55.953 --> 01:52:56.995
Now!

01:52:56.996 --> 01:52:58.496
Yes, sir!

01:52:59.623 --> 01:53:02.209
Let's go, let's go!
Move your butts! Move it!

01:53:05.046 --> 01:53:06.088
Stand.

01:53:07.215 --> 01:53:08.466
Well?

01:53:11.845 --> 01:53:12.970
Well, what?

01:53:13.054 --> 01:53:16.515
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

01:53:17.559 --> 01:53:19.185
He must have said something.

01:53:19.269 --> 01:53:21.312
No, sir, Warden.

01:53:21.396 --> 01:53:22.855
Not a word.

01:53:24.858 --> 01:53:26.859
Lord, it's a miracle!

01:53:27.903 --> 01:53:30.362
A man up and vanished like a fart in the wind.

01:53:30.447 --> 01:53:32.198
Nothing left but...

01:53:32.282 --> 01:53:35.201
some damn rocks on a windowsill.

01:53:35.285 --> 01:53:37.036
And that cupcake on the wall.

01:53:37.120 --> 01:53:38.746
Let's ask her.

01:53:38.830 --> 01:53:42.792
Maybe she knows. What say there,
Fuzzy Britches? Feel like talking?

01:53:43.877 --> 01:53:44.960
Ah...

01:53:44.961 --> 01:53:46.420
I guess not.

01:53:46.505 --> 01:53:49.381
Why should she be any different?

01:53:49.466 --> 01:53:51.926
This is a conspiracy.

01:53:52.010 --> 01:53:54.220
That's what this is.

01:53:54.304 --> 01:53:55.846
One big...

01:53:55.931 --> 01:53:58.683
damn conspiracy!

01:53:58.768 --> 01:54:01.436
And everyone's in on it!

01:54:01.521 --> 01:54:02.813
Including her!

01:54:37.473 --> 01:54:39.349
In 1966,

01:54:39.433 --> 01:54:42.102
Andy Dufresne escaped

01:54:42.186 --> 01:54:44.271
from Shawshank Prison.

01:54:45.940 --> 01:54:48.692
All they found of him
was a muddy set of prison clothes,

01:54:48.776 --> 01:54:50.819
a bar of soap

01:54:50.903 --> 01:54:55.282
and an old rock hammer
damn near worn down to the nub.

01:54:59.663 --> 01:55:04.500
I remember thinking it would take a man
600 years to tunnel through the wall with it.

01:55:04.585 --> 01:55:07.295
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

01:55:25.856 --> 01:55:27.940
Oh, Andy loved geology.

01:55:28.984 --> 01:55:32.486
I imagine it appealed to his meticulous nature.

01:55:32.571 --> 01:55:34.864
An Ice Age here,

01:55:34.948 --> 01:55:37.533
a million years of mountain-building there.

01:55:38.577 --> 01:55:40.995
Geology is the study of pressure and time.

01:55:42.205 --> 01:55:44.248
That's all it takes, really.

01:55:44.333 --> 01:55:46.375
Pressure...

01:55:46.460 --> 01:55:48.336
and time.

01:55:48.420 --> 01:55:51.756
That and a big goddamn poster.

01:55:54.969 --> 01:55:56.345
Like I said,

01:55:56.346 --> 01:56:00.140
in prison, a man will do most anything
to keep his mind occupied.

01:56:02.936 --> 01:56:08.106
It turns out Andy's favorite hobby
was toting his wall out into the exercise yard.

01:56:08.191 --> 01:56:10.275
A handful at a time.

01:56:12.111 --> 01:56:14.279
I guess after Tommy was killed,

01:56:14.364 --> 01:56:17.199
Andy decided he'd been here
just about long enough.

01:56:17.283 --> 01:56:19.493
Lickety-split. I want to get home.

01:56:20.787 --> 01:56:22.871
I'm just about finished, sir.

01:56:44.268 --> 01:56:46.353
Three deposits tonight.

01:56:53.529 --> 01:56:55.571
Andy did like he was told.

01:56:56.615 --> 01:57:00.118
Buffed those shoes to a high mirror shine.

01:57:03.706 --> 01:57:05.748
The guard simply didn't notice.

01:57:05.833 --> 01:57:07.875
Neither did I.

01:57:07.960 --> 01:57:12.296
I mean, seriously, how often
do you really look at a man's shoes?

01:59:16.340 --> 01:59:22.512
Andy crawled to freedom through 500 yards
of shit-smelling foulness I can't even imagine.

01:59:23.848 --> 01:59:25.849
Or maybe I just don't want to.

01:59:30.563 --> 01:59:32.772
500 yards.

01:59:33.816 --> 01:59:36.317
That's the length of five football fields.

01:59:37.361 --> 01:59:39.612
Just shy of half a mile.

02:00:34.836 --> 02:00:39.381
The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her little secret,

02:00:39.466 --> 02:00:42.885
a man nobody ever laid eyes on before

02:00:42.969 --> 02:00:45.388
strode into the Maine National Bank.

02:00:45.473 --> 02:00:47.515
Until that moment,

02:00:47.600 --> 02:00:49.476
he didn't exist,

02:00:49.560 --> 02:00:50.894
except on paper.

02:00:50.978 --> 02:00:52.020
May I help you?

02:00:52.104 --> 02:00:54.147
He had all the proper ID,

02:00:54.232 --> 02:00:57.859
driver's license, birth certificate,
social security card.

02:00:57.944 --> 02:01:01.238
And the signature was a spot-on match.

02:01:01.322 --> 02:01:04.366
I must say, I'm sorry to be losing your business.

02:01:04.450 --> 02:01:06.451
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

02:01:06.535 --> 02:01:08.328
Thank you.

02:01:08.412 --> 02:01:10.205
I'm sure I will.

02:01:10.289 --> 02:01:12.415
Here's your cashier's check, sir.

02:01:12.500 --> 02:01:14.542
Will there be anything else?

02:01:14.627 --> 02:01:15.627
Please...

02:01:15.711 --> 02:01:18.797
Would you add this to your outgoing mail?

02:01:18.881 --> 02:01:21.091
I'd be happy to.

02:01:21.175 --> 02:01:23.510
- Good day, sir.
- Good day.

02:01:23.594 --> 02:01:28.390
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.

02:01:29.558 --> 02:01:36.022
All told, he blew town with better than $370,000
of Warden Norton's money.

02:01:36.107 --> 02:01:38.566
Severance pay for 19 years.

02:01:46.702 --> 02:01:48.995
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

02:02:41.716 --> 02:02:44.718
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

02:02:44.802 --> 02:02:49.431
If you give up the right to remain silent, anything
you say will be held against you in court.

02:02:49.515 --> 02:02:51.391
I wasn't there to see it.

02:02:51.476 --> 02:02:56.355
But I hear Byron Hadley started sobbing
like a little girl when they took him away.

02:03:01.778 --> 02:03:04.571
Norton had no intention of going that quietly.

02:03:20.546 --> 02:03:22.005
Samuel Norton?

02:03:22.090 --> 02:03:25.342
We have a warrant for your arrest. Open up.

02:03:28.221 --> 02:03:29.346
Norton!

02:03:29.430 --> 02:03:31.098
Open the door.

02:03:31.182 --> 02:03:32.933
I'm not sure which key it is.

02:03:35.812 --> 02:03:37.479
Norton!

02:03:42.945 --> 02:03:45.029
Make it easy on yourself, Norton.

02:03:56.333 --> 02:03:59.919
I like to think
the last thing that went through his head,

02:04:00.003 --> 02:04:01.712
other than that bullet,

02:04:01.797 --> 02:04:05.800
was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

02:04:07.469 --> 02:04:08.553
Carter, James...

02:04:08.637 --> 02:04:12.014
Not long after the Warden
deprived us of his company,

02:04:12.099 --> 02:04:14.350
I got a postcard in the mail.

02:04:16.061 --> 02:04:18.479
It was blank but the postmark said...

02:04:18.564 --> 02:04:21.315
Fort Hancock, Texas.

02:04:21.400 --> 02:04:23.443
Fort Hancock.

02:04:23.527 --> 02:04:25.570
Right on the border.

02:04:25.654 --> 02:04:27.697
That's where Andy crossed.

02:04:27.781 --> 02:04:31.659
When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down,

02:04:32.703 --> 02:04:34.787
it always makes me laugh.

02:04:36.206 --> 02:04:38.250
Andy Dufresne,

02:04:38.334 --> 02:04:40.711
who crawled through a river of shit

02:04:40.795 --> 02:04:42.880
and came out clean on the other side.

02:04:44.090 --> 02:04:46.133
Andy Dufresne,

02:04:46.217 --> 02:04:48.135
headed for the Pacific.

02:04:50.722 --> 02:04:52.764
Hadley's got him by the toes, right?

02:04:52.849 --> 02:04:57.060
And he says, "I believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident."

02:04:57.145 --> 02:05:00.314
Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.

02:05:00.398 --> 02:05:02.649
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

02:05:02.734 --> 02:05:05.235
"These friends of mine
could use a couple of beers!"

02:05:05.320 --> 02:05:07.404
- And he got it.
- And he got it!

02:05:08.573 --> 02:05:10.949
Sometimes it makes me sad, though,

02:05:11.034 --> 02:05:13.076
Andy being gone.

02:05:13.161 --> 02:05:17.164
I have to remind myself
that some birds aren't meant to be caged.

02:05:18.249 --> 02:05:20.334
Their feathers are just too bright.

02:05:21.878 --> 02:05:23.921
And when they fly away,

02:05:24.005 --> 02:05:27.925
the part of you that knows
it was a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

02:05:29.677 --> 02:05:31.136
But still...

02:05:31.221 --> 02:05:35.391
the place you live in is that much more drab
and empty that they're gone.

02:05:39.939 --> 02:05:42.190
I guess I just miss my friend.

02:06:06.173 --> 02:06:08.049
Please sit down.

02:06:13.639 --> 02:06:15.765
Ellis Boyd Redding.

02:06:15.849 --> 02:06:19.227
Your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

02:06:19.311 --> 02:06:21.688
Do you feel you've been rehabilitated?

02:06:23.816 --> 02:06:25.900
Rehabilitated?

02:06:27.444 --> 02:06:29.529
Well, now, let me see.

02:06:30.573 --> 02:06:32.907
You know, I don't have any idea
what that means.

02:06:34.703 --> 02:06:37.246
Well, it means you're ready to rejoin society...

02:06:37.330 --> 02:06:39.873
I know what you think it means, sonny.

02:06:42.252 --> 02:06:44.336
To me, it's just a made-up word.

02:06:45.380 --> 02:06:47.631
A politician's word so that...

02:06:47.716 --> 02:06:53.220
young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie and have a job.

02:06:55.640 --> 02:06:57.725
What do you really want to know?

02:06:58.893 --> 02:07:00.811
Am I sorry for what I did?

02:07:00.895 --> 02:07:02.605
Well, are you?

02:07:04.232 --> 02:07:06.817
There's not a day goes by I don't feel regret.

02:07:08.403 --> 02:07:11.530
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

02:07:15.327 --> 02:07:17.411
I look back on the way I was then.

02:07:19.998 --> 02:07:22.041
A young...

02:07:22.125 --> 02:07:25.210
stupid kid who committed that terrible crime.

02:07:29.049 --> 02:07:31.133
I wanna talk to him.

02:07:32.511 --> 02:07:34.679
I wanna try and talk some sense to him,

02:07:35.723 --> 02:07:37.807
tell him the way things are.

02:07:39.977 --> 02:07:42.062
But I can't.

02:07:43.272 --> 02:07:45.357
That kid's long gone.

02:07:46.651 --> 02:07:48.735
This old man is all that's left.

02:07:50.863 --> 02:07:52.364
I gotta live with that.

02:07:53.699 --> 02:07:55.492
Rehabilitated?

02:07:55.576 --> 02:07:57.577
It's just a bullshit word.

02:07:57.662 --> 02:08:03.583
So you go on and stamp your form, sonny,
and stop wasting my time.

02:08:04.669 --> 02:08:06.711
Because to tell you the truth,

02:08:06.796 --> 02:08:09.297
I don't give a shit.

02:09:35.511 --> 02:09:37.596
Here you go, miss.

02:09:39.599 --> 02:09:41.057
Rest room break, boss?

02:09:47.106 --> 02:09:51.401
You don't need to ask me every time you need
to go take a piss. Just go. Understand?

02:09:52.612 --> 02:09:54.279
Yes, sir.

02:10:04.332 --> 02:10:07.375
40 years
I've been asking permission to piss.

02:10:08.377 --> 02:10:10.587
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

02:10:14.717 --> 02:10:16.802
There's a harsh truth to face.

02:10:18.763 --> 02:10:21.097
No way I'm gonna make it on the outside.

02:10:29.316 --> 02:10:32.777
All I do any more
is think of ways to break my parole...

02:10:33.821 --> 02:10:35.905
..so maybe they'd send me back.

02:10:41.411 --> 02:10:43.496
A terrible thing to live in fear.

02:10:44.873 --> 02:10:48.251
Brooks Hatlen knew it, knew it all too well.

02:10:50.420 --> 02:10:53.214
All I want is to be back
where things make sense,

02:10:54.258 --> 02:10:56.759
where I won't have to be afraid all the time.

02:10:59.638 --> 02:11:01.722
Only one thing stops me.

02:11:02.766 --> 02:11:04.851
A promise I made to Andy.

02:11:25.582 --> 02:11:27.666
Here it is.

02:11:37.468 --> 02:11:39.553
Much obliged, sir.

02:15:18.360 --> 02:15:19.652
Dear Red,

02:15:19.736 --> 02:15:22.196
if you're reading this, you've gotten out.

02:15:22.280 --> 02:15:26.534
And if you've come this far,
maybe you're willing to come a little further.

02:15:26.618 --> 02:15:29.203
You remember the name of the town, don't you?

02:15:31.498 --> 02:15:33.582
Zihuatanejo.

02:15:34.626 --> 02:15:35.835
I could use a good man

02:15:35.919 --> 02:15:37.962
to help me get my project on wheels.

02:15:38.046 --> 02:15:40.172
I'll keep an eye out for you

02:15:40.257 --> 02:15:42.299
and the chessboard ready.

02:15:43.343 --> 02:15:44.718
Remember, Red,

02:15:44.803 --> 02:15:46.846
hope is a good thing.

02:15:46.930 --> 02:15:48.973
Maybe the best of things.

02:15:49.057 --> 02:15:51.142
And no good thing ever dies.

02:15:52.185 --> 02:15:54.645
I will be hoping that this letter finds you

02:15:54.729 --> 02:15:56.772
and finds you well.

02:15:56.857 --> 02:15:59.358
Your friend, Andy.

02:16:33.936 --> 02:16:37.814
Get busy living or get busy dying.

02:16:40.318 --> 02:16:42.402
That's goddamn right.

02:16:47.909 --> 02:16:50.035
For the second time in my life,

02:16:50.119 --> 02:16:52.204
I'm guilty of committing a crime.

02:16:53.873 --> 02:16:55.957
Parole violation.

02:16:55.958 --> 02:16:59.669
Of course, I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.

02:17:00.922 --> 02:17:02.964
Not for an old crook like me.

02:17:03.049 --> 02:17:05.133
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

02:17:08.846 --> 02:17:12.975
I find I'm so excited I can barely sit still
or hold a thought in my head.

02:17:14.019 --> 02:17:17.021
I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.

02:17:17.105 --> 02:17:19.815
A free man at the start of a long journey

02:17:19.900 --> 02:17:22.818
whose conclusion is uncertain.

02:17:25.697 --> 02:17:27.865
I hope I can make it across the border.

02:17:29.743 --> 02:17:32.536
I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.

02:17:34.915 --> 02:17:38.125
I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.

02:17:40.879 --> 02:17:42.755
I hope.
